WEBVTT

00:26.901 --> 00:30.905
[piano music playing]

00:51.384 --> 00:56.806
♪ Today is markin' day ♪

01:01.728 --> 01:07.650
♪ Our eyes finally see ♪

01:11.571 --> 01:17.285
♪ A future with someone ♪

01:21.372 --> 01:27.712
♪ Where I fit perfectly ♪

01:31.591 --> 01:38.056
♪ And for so long,
I have waited ♪

01:42.685 --> 01:47.982
♪ Heard your lonely call ♪

01:52.445 --> 01:57.784
♪ Heard it cross the ocean ♪

02:02.080 --> 02:08.628
♪ Through a hundred million walls ♪

02:09.671 --> 02:16.678
♪ And I was made for you ♪

02:19.722 --> 02:26.729
♪ And I was made for you ♪

02:29.941 --> 02:36.948
♪ And I was made for you ♪

02:39.701 --> 02:44.247
♪ For you, you ♪

02:44.330 --> 02:48.084
♪ Ahh ♪

02:57.886 --> 02:59.888
["For the Love of You"
by The Isley Brothers playing]

02:59.971 --> 03:01.639
♪ Yeah ♪

03:01.723 --> 03:04.851
♪ Well, well, well ♪

03:04.934 --> 03:07.145
♪ Yeah ♪

03:09.606 --> 03:11.065
♪ Yeah ♪

03:12.108 --> 03:13.693
♪ Hey... ♪

03:13.776 --> 03:15.820
Mmm. It smells good in here.

03:15.904 --> 03:17.322
Oh.

03:18.740 --> 03:21.492
Aren't you beautiful? Mmm.

03:21.576 --> 03:24.495
Does my wife know you're here?

03:24.954 --> 03:26.164
Don't tell her.

03:26.247 --> 03:27.624
I won't say a word.

03:29.542 --> 03:31.336
♪ Yeah ♪

03:31.419 --> 03:32.503
Hey, baby.

03:32.587 --> 03:33.922
Hey.

03:34.005 --> 03:35.381
How's your day?

03:36.007 --> 03:37.592
So much better
now that you're cooking.

03:38.635 --> 03:41.304
Well, you have a front-row seat
to an adventure.

03:41.387 --> 03:42.680
[laughs]

03:42.764 --> 03:45.016
You look like you have it handled.

03:45.099 --> 03:48.394
Yeah, well,
that would be a stretch.

03:49.437 --> 03:54.108
♪ Yeah, so very long ♪

03:54.192 --> 03:55.735
♪ Well ♪

03:55.818 --> 03:57.654
♪ Ooh ♪

03:57.737 --> 03:59.864
♪ Glad to be ♪

04:00.949 --> 04:02.492
♪ Here alone ♪

04:02.575 --> 04:06.663
♪ With a lover like no other ♪

04:06.746 --> 04:09.499
-Ready?
-♪ Sad to see... ♪

04:09.582 --> 04:11.459
[laughs]

04:11.542 --> 04:13.461
You still got it.

04:14.712 --> 04:16.089
What would I do without you?

04:17.674 --> 04:18.800
One sec.

04:18.883 --> 04:22.428
♪ I wanna be livin'... ♪

04:22.512 --> 04:24.138
[imitates whip]

04:24.222 --> 04:25.682
Oh.

04:26.849 --> 04:28.309
[chuckles]

04:28.393 --> 04:32.188
♪ All that I'm givin' ♪

04:32.272 --> 04:35.692
-What are you up to?
-♪ Is for the love of you ♪

04:36.067 --> 04:37.986
♪ All right, now... ♪

04:38.069 --> 04:40.697
Okay, honey,
can--can I open yet?

04:40.780 --> 04:41.990
-Almost.
-All right.

04:42.073 --> 04:44.075
[song fades]

04:46.286 --> 04:47.704
Can I open now?

04:48.997 --> 04:51.916
[gasps]
You didn't! Stop!

04:52.000 --> 04:53.167
I did.

04:53.251 --> 04:55.169
Oh, my gosh.

04:56.296 --> 04:57.505
It's beautiful.

04:57.588 --> 04:59.215
Now I know
you wanted the black one,

04:59.299 --> 05:01.092
but, I mean, look at it.

05:01.175 --> 05:03.344
It's so breathtaking,
and it matches the house,

05:03.428 --> 05:04.929
and, plus,

05:05.263 --> 05:08.558
"For those colors
which you wish to be beautiful,

05:08.641 --> 05:13.438
always first prepare
a pure white ground."

05:13.521 --> 05:15.857
Only you would quote Leonardo.

05:15.940 --> 05:19.235
Okay, let's see
what my money's been paying for.

05:19.319 --> 05:22.989
Okay, it's only been two months, but...

05:23.990 --> 05:25.366
I'll play you something

05:25.450 --> 05:27.744
my mother used to play for me
when I was a kid

05:27.827 --> 05:28.786
that put me to sleep.

05:28.870 --> 05:30.872
[playing piano]

05:36.461 --> 05:39.464
Oh, I--Nah, that's beautiful.
You're good.

05:39.547 --> 05:41.716
Thanks.
I'm still working on that.

05:41.799 --> 05:44.719
I'm gonna play that
for our little girl.

05:47.597 --> 05:49.557
Now a little something for you.

05:49.640 --> 05:51.017
Okay.

05:51.100 --> 05:54.562
[playing "For the Love of You"]

05:55.480 --> 05:57.190
I know that.

05:57.273 --> 05:59.275
[joins in]

06:03.613 --> 06:04.781
[misplayed notes]

06:04.864 --> 06:06.282
-[groans]
-Whoa, whoa.

06:06.365 --> 06:07.992
[laughs]

06:08.076 --> 06:10.119
That--That wasn't it.

06:10.203 --> 06:11.788
Okay,
I'm working on that part.

06:11.871 --> 06:13.748
Okay. All right.
[smoke alarm beeping]

06:13.831 --> 06:15.792
Honey, you need
to go check on the noodles

06:15.875 --> 06:17.126
before you burn the house down.

06:17.210 --> 06:19.253
[laughs]

06:19.337 --> 06:23.049
I just wanted it to be
a special anniversary, you know?

06:23.132 --> 06:24.258
First one in our new house.

06:24.342 --> 06:26.511
It's the thought that counts.

06:26.594 --> 06:29.472
Pizza, wine, candlelight.

06:30.306 --> 06:32.809
Speaking of our new house,

06:32.892 --> 06:35.478
I want to make this house a home.

06:36.604 --> 06:39.148
I want us to start a family.

06:39.232 --> 06:41.234
Oh, come on.
You know how I feel

06:41.317 --> 06:43.319
about having children right now.

06:43.402 --> 06:45.196
Eventually, yeah,
but right now--

06:45.279 --> 06:47.907
You would be such a good dad.

06:49.325 --> 06:53.037
Yeah, as long
as I don't turn out like mine.

06:53.121 --> 06:56.874
Stop. That's all the more reason
why you wouldn't.

06:56.958 --> 06:58.126
-No, I--
-You know that--

06:58.209 --> 07:00.336
-Madison!
-Okay.

07:00.419 --> 07:01.879
I'm sorry.

07:01.963 --> 07:04.632
♪ The way you touch me,
baby... ♪

07:04.715 --> 07:06.634
I don't think
you'll ever understand this.

07:06.717 --> 07:08.094
Don't do that.

07:08.177 --> 07:10.930
If anyone understands what it's like
to lose a parent, it's me.

07:11.013 --> 07:14.183
I feel really bad about my dad.

07:14.267 --> 07:15.393
I never see him.

07:16.102 --> 07:17.895
Well, I told you,

07:18.020 --> 07:21.732
if you want to bring him back
to come live with us, we can.

07:22.024 --> 07:24.652
No. I don't want
to complicate things.

07:24.735 --> 07:27.029
It puts a lot of pressure on us.

07:28.364 --> 07:29.824
They called today.

07:31.075 --> 07:33.453
They said that he was doing fine.

07:33.536 --> 07:34.829
Well, let's go see.

07:36.747 --> 07:40.501
Let's go down there this weekend
and pay him a visit.

07:41.669 --> 07:43.546
-Really?
-Really.

07:53.347 --> 07:55.016
This guy.

08:03.858 --> 08:05.735
Please be positive.

08:06.027 --> 08:08.237
Please be positive.

08:09.280 --> 08:10.990
Who you talking to?

08:11.073 --> 08:12.700
[laughs] You scared me.

08:13.534 --> 08:15.703
Stupid pregnancy tests.

08:16.120 --> 08:18.164
Oh, yeah?
Did it say anything back?

08:18.247 --> 08:20.333
Still waiting.

08:20.625 --> 08:22.835
[imitates clock ticking]

08:22.919 --> 08:25.379
Listen, when it's meant to be,
it'll happen.

08:25.963 --> 08:29.634
Hey, you know that I've wanted
to have kids since I was five.

08:29.717 --> 08:31.093
I know.

08:36.891 --> 08:38.559
[chuckles]

08:38.643 --> 08:39.852
Anything new?

08:39.936 --> 08:42.146
Still no little Michael.

08:42.230 --> 08:45.983
And we will have one
when it's time, all right?

08:46.067 --> 08:47.610
But don't force it.

08:47.693 --> 08:51.197
In the meantime, I love you,

08:51.948 --> 08:54.033
and we have a lot of time to practice

08:54.909 --> 08:57.161
and practice and practice...

08:58.287 --> 08:59.330
and practice some more,

08:59.413 --> 09:01.832
but right now,
I gotta get ready for work.

09:01.916 --> 09:03.626
Mm-mm. What about practice?

09:03.709 --> 09:05.878
Hmm. We're having practice?
Let's go rock--

09:05.962 --> 09:07.463
I gotta get ready for work.
Come on.

09:07.547 --> 09:09.549
-Okay, I love you.
-I love you, too, baby.

09:44.125 --> 09:45.293
Hi, Mom.

09:49.547 --> 09:51.382
You'd be so proud right now.

09:53.926 --> 09:57.680
I got that promotion
I was telling you about.

09:57.763 --> 09:59.557
And they're
gonna make me partner.

10:03.853 --> 10:09.150
I'm now head of my household,
like you always taught me to be.

10:14.989 --> 10:16.449
Madison quit her job,

10:16.532 --> 10:20.244
and now she's gonna be able
to be a full-time wife.

10:21.412 --> 10:23.331
I think I'm gonna be okay.

10:25.499 --> 10:27.293
I love you, Mom.

10:52.234 --> 10:53.986
[sighs]

11:04.789 --> 11:06.165
[music playing]

11:06.248 --> 11:09.126
Surprise!

11:09.210 --> 11:12.129
You didn't think I wasn't gonna
get you for last year, did you?

11:12.213 --> 11:13.464
I didn't.

11:15.341 --> 11:18.094
You know I don't like surprises, baby.

11:18.177 --> 11:20.846
I know, honey, but I just had to.

11:20.930 --> 11:22.932
♪ I cannot explain
the way I feel... ♪

11:23.015 --> 11:24.642
If it isn't the man of the hour.

11:24.725 --> 11:26.268
Thank you. Thank you.
Hi, Chelsea.

11:26.352 --> 11:27.937
How's everything
down at the hospital?

11:28.020 --> 11:29.397
Things are going great.

11:30.189 --> 11:32.400
You know, there's always
room for Madison

11:32.775 --> 11:34.527
if you ever decide
to let her work again.

11:34.610 --> 11:37.613
Ah, but then I won't have her
all to myself. Right, baby?

11:37.696 --> 11:41.534
Right. I just wish Michael
would give me a little Michael.

11:41.617 --> 11:43.411
Every day.
I hear it every day.

11:43.494 --> 11:44.745
-Yes, he does.
-Yeah.

11:44.829 --> 11:46.997
You sure you want to ruin
that perfect figure, girl?

11:47.081 --> 11:49.625
Ah, listen to your friend.
She knows what she's talking about.

11:49.708 --> 11:51.335
Speaking of friends...

11:51.419 --> 11:54.004
Oh! Hey, man!

11:54.171 --> 11:55.214
I need one of those.

11:55.297 --> 11:57.091
Let's get you one of these.

11:58.884 --> 12:00.761
[sighs]

12:00.845 --> 12:02.596
Madison...

12:04.890 --> 12:06.725
you have the perfect husband.

12:07.601 --> 12:09.228
You know, sometimes I think

12:09.645 --> 12:11.772
maybe he's a little too perfect.

12:11.856 --> 12:14.150
Girl, stop hatin'
'cause you are single.

12:14.233 --> 12:18.028
Oh. Okay, I am enjoying
the single life, thank you.

12:18.112 --> 12:20.030
-I heard.
-[laughs]

12:21.323 --> 12:24.660
But as my mom always said,

12:25.661 --> 12:28.038
"Keep an eye out
on those good boys.

12:29.165 --> 12:31.041
They may turn out to be bad."

12:31.250 --> 12:34.211
Not this one.
That's why I married him.

12:36.922 --> 12:38.424
Okay.

12:39.508 --> 12:40.926
To the good boys.

12:41.010 --> 12:42.553
To the good ones.

12:43.387 --> 12:44.889
♪ Love ♪

12:44.972 --> 12:46.348
-♪ You keep giving me... ♪
-[cheering]

12:46.432 --> 12:48.017
All right, all right,
all right, all right.

12:48.100 --> 12:50.269
All right, hold on. Hold on.
Let's take this opportunity

12:50.769 --> 12:52.813
to give my good boy Mike here

12:52.897 --> 12:55.483
and his beautiful,
beautiful bride a toast.

12:55.816 --> 12:57.067
[cheering]

12:57.151 --> 12:58.652
Yeah.

12:58.736 --> 13:00.863
-To the happy couple.
-Thanks, brother.

13:00.946 --> 13:02.698
♪ You can forget
about your problems, babe ♪

13:02.781 --> 13:04.533
♪ Just me and you ♪

13:04.617 --> 13:08.454
♪ Let's make this last, oh ho ♪

13:08.537 --> 13:12.708
♪ 'Cause you know I can't
live without your love ♪

13:12.791 --> 13:14.668
♪ Your love ♪

13:14.752 --> 13:16.837
♪ Your love ♪

13:16.921 --> 13:19.215
-♪ You keep giving me ♪
-♪ You keep giving me ♪

13:19.298 --> 13:22.092
♪ Your love, your love ♪

13:22.176 --> 13:24.470
♪ Your love ♪

13:24.762 --> 13:26.347
[piano music playing]

13:27.515 --> 13:29.475
[Madison and Michael laugh]

13:29.558 --> 13:31.101
I hope you liked today.

13:32.102 --> 13:33.103
I did.

13:33.729 --> 13:35.981
I gotta admit I did.

13:37.358 --> 13:38.859
Now it's my turn.

13:42.404 --> 13:44.990
Babe, you didn't have to do this.

13:45.074 --> 13:46.617
You already got me the piano.

13:46.700 --> 13:49.453
Yeah, I know,
but it reminded me of us,

13:49.537 --> 13:51.956
and I couldn't resist it.

13:53.624 --> 13:56.752
Anyway, I'm trying
to give you the world, so...

14:03.300 --> 14:05.636
"Til Death Do Us Part."

14:10.015 --> 14:11.600
Here.

14:15.604 --> 14:19.650
You know, you are everything to me.

14:21.986 --> 14:23.696
-Help me with your hair?
-Mm-hmm.

14:29.034 --> 14:32.788
And you are the only good thing

14:32.872 --> 14:35.541
that's happened to me
in my entire life.

14:38.294 --> 14:40.629
Can't imagine life without you.

14:41.839 --> 14:43.173
You mean that?

14:43.257 --> 14:44.258
I mean that.

14:51.140 --> 14:52.224
I love you.

14:53.684 --> 14:55.311
I love you.

14:56.562 --> 14:58.522
[mellow R &amp; B playing]

14:58.606 --> 15:00.190
[laughs]

15:00.274 --> 15:03.027
These just came
in the mail today.

15:03.110 --> 15:04.320
Oh!

15:04.403 --> 15:05.779
My God, they're so cute.

15:05.863 --> 15:07.740
Is this the only color
they had at the store?

15:07.823 --> 15:08.991
[both laugh]

15:09.074 --> 15:10.534
You know
I'm obsessed with red.

15:10.618 --> 15:12.328
Oh, my God.

15:12.411 --> 15:13.871
Wow!

15:13.954 --> 15:16.498
Okay, no judgment, but, um,

15:17.124 --> 15:19.418
don't you think you should
wait til you're pregnant first?

15:19.501 --> 15:21.128
I just had to get these.

15:21.211 --> 15:24.131
I could just see my little one
prancing around. It's--

15:24.214 --> 15:26.634
Oh, my God. And what if
you have a boy first, hmm?

15:26.717 --> 15:28.469
I don't know.
I can worry about that later.

15:28.552 --> 15:30.930
-Of course.
-[laughs]

15:32.389 --> 15:33.724
♪ Reminisce about the times ♪

15:33.807 --> 15:35.434
♪ We was goin'
through the struggles ♪

15:35.517 --> 15:37.728
♪ Since a young boy,
you was in and out of trouble ♪

15:37.811 --> 15:40.773
♪ Hangin' with the wrong crowd,
now you gotta do the time ♪

15:40.856 --> 15:43.359
♪ Hitting licks on the streets,
tell me what was on your mind ♪

15:43.442 --> 15:45.653
♪ I never could imagine
seein' you in jail ♪

15:45.736 --> 15:48.155
♪ I was by your side
when you needed bail ♪

15:48.238 --> 15:50.574
♪ You should have seen the pain
that you put on my... ♪

15:50.658 --> 15:53.327
Hey, hey, hey.
Brought you some water.

15:54.662 --> 15:57.247
Ah, wow, thank you.

15:58.248 --> 15:59.500
Ohh.

16:00.125 --> 16:02.461
Ah. You know I can't drink water

16:02.544 --> 16:04.046
-without my mint.
-"Without my mint."

16:04.129 --> 16:06.423
Sorry, babe. I forgot.

16:07.049 --> 16:08.884
It's not like you to forget, though.
You okay?

16:08.968 --> 16:09.969
Yeah, I'm fine.

16:16.850 --> 16:18.560
You working me out or that bag?

16:18.644 --> 16:19.895
[laughs]

16:19.979 --> 16:20.938
You're next.

16:21.021 --> 16:22.690
-Mmm.
-[chuckles]

16:22.773 --> 16:23.941
Okay, I'll be back.

16:24.024 --> 16:25.109
All right. Thank you.

16:25.192 --> 16:26.276
-I love you.
-I love you.

16:29.279 --> 16:32.032
♪ Give me the feeling... ♪

16:32.116 --> 16:33.826
[man laughs]

16:35.035 --> 16:37.037
Oh, man, yeah.

16:37.121 --> 16:38.831
Yeah, but we had our share,
though, didn't we?

16:38.914 --> 16:40.040
We had our share.

16:40.124 --> 16:42.292
Oh, man, wow.

16:42.793 --> 16:46.422
Whatever happened to,
"Me? I ain't never getting married.

16:46.505 --> 16:48.632
"I ain't never letting
none of these ho's

16:48.716 --> 16:51.385
run this show over here.
I run my shit."

16:51.468 --> 16:53.012
[imitates muttering]

16:53.095 --> 16:55.764
Yeah, that guy?
That guy was shocked, too.

16:57.474 --> 16:59.101
You know, but...

17:00.561 --> 17:02.646
I mean, I'm sure
you remember what,

17:02.730 --> 17:04.440
you know,
what happened with my parents.

17:05.524 --> 17:06.650
Yeah.

17:07.401 --> 17:09.445
And, um, I'm not really sure

17:09.528 --> 17:13.240
I ever let on
how bad that was for me.

17:17.578 --> 17:22.249
But that took me
to a really dark place, man.

17:23.792 --> 17:25.961
Oh, man, sitting up here,
crying like a bitch.

17:26.045 --> 17:27.504
Nah, 'cause you feel--

17:27.588 --> 17:29.590
I mean, you feel
what you gotta feel.

17:31.175 --> 17:33.135
But then when I met her, man,

17:33.719 --> 17:36.722
it's like my light came back on,
you know.

17:36.805 --> 17:38.766
Yeah, the right one
will do that for you.

17:38.849 --> 17:40.309
Yeah, she changed everything.

17:41.518 --> 17:44.104
But she tells me that, um--

17:44.188 --> 17:47.733
that your business has you
traveling all over the world.

17:47.816 --> 17:49.234
Yeah, yes, sir.

17:50.235 --> 17:52.362
So what is it that you do now,
Mr. Traveler?

17:52.446 --> 17:54.698
I've got a digital security
company, man,

17:54.782 --> 17:57.493
little private protection

17:57.576 --> 18:01.371
mixed with a little, uh,
you know, private investigation.

18:01.455 --> 18:04.541
Little rich kids run away,
we gotta find their dumb asses.

18:04.625 --> 18:05.918
Still protecting people.

18:06.001 --> 18:06.877
But you know what?

18:07.377 --> 18:08.962
I travel a lot.

18:09.046 --> 18:12.508
My wife hates it,
but I get to choose my clients.

18:13.550 --> 18:15.761
What--What happened to, um...

18:16.762 --> 18:17.888
Leslie...

18:17.971 --> 18:18.889
Smith.

18:18.972 --> 18:20.099
No, no. It was Johnson.

18:20.182 --> 18:21.975
No, no, Leslie Smith, bro.

18:22.059 --> 18:24.228
Oh! [laughs]

18:24.311 --> 18:26.146
You followed through!

18:26.230 --> 18:28.232
-Yes, sir.
-Okay, okay.

18:28.315 --> 18:30.526
Well, hey, you got kids?

18:30.609 --> 18:32.528
Absolutely. Two. Look at that.

18:33.654 --> 18:35.364
-Man.
-What about y'all?

18:36.031 --> 18:37.407
Y'all wanna have some kids?

18:37.491 --> 18:39.326
Not right now. I--

18:41.036 --> 18:42.746
I don't want a kid right now.

18:43.372 --> 18:44.873
I just want my wife.

18:44.957 --> 18:47.960
Oh, he's being a selfish bastard.

18:48.043 --> 18:49.711
I know. I know.

18:49.795 --> 18:52.673
I'll admit I'm a control freak.

18:54.049 --> 18:57.010
But, you know, I--I do love her.

18:57.094 --> 18:59.388
I love her. I really do.
I want to give her everything.

18:59.471 --> 19:01.140
Everything...

19:01.223 --> 19:02.766
-but some kids?
-[chuckles]

19:02.850 --> 19:04.434
Nah, I hear you, bro.

19:04.518 --> 19:06.728
But, you know, we gotta
think about how they feel.

19:06.812 --> 19:08.772
It's all about what they want, too.

19:10.732 --> 19:12.568
Yeah.

19:13.443 --> 19:15.070
I just don't know what to do.

19:16.280 --> 19:17.739
Tell her the truth.

19:19.074 --> 19:20.367
Just tell her the truth, man.

19:20.450 --> 19:22.327
Listen, what I've learned in marriage

19:22.411 --> 19:27.666
is that the key to success
is communication, 100%.

19:29.126 --> 19:32.796
Look, I--I don't have any secrets
that I keep from my wife.

19:34.131 --> 19:37.759
[both laugh]

19:37.843 --> 19:40.554
Okay. I--I know--

19:40.637 --> 19:43.223
I know there's at least two secrets

19:43.307 --> 19:46.351
that you got right now
you didn't dare tell that lady.

19:46.435 --> 19:47.853
She wouldn't have married you.

19:49.104 --> 19:50.439
Oh, man.

19:50.522 --> 19:51.982
You're right.

19:54.151 --> 19:55.360
I gotta be honest with her.

19:56.737 --> 19:58.614
And honest with yourself, too, bro.

19:58.697 --> 20:00.282
That's the key.

20:03.118 --> 20:04.328
Cheers.

20:04.411 --> 20:06.330
Absolutely.

20:09.458 --> 20:10.876
Hey, babe.

20:16.006 --> 20:19.301
Listen. Um, we need to talk.

20:19.384 --> 20:21.303
Yeah, we sure do need to talk.

20:22.554 --> 20:24.181
Excuse me?

20:29.937 --> 20:31.563
Why would you lie to me, Michael?

20:32.773 --> 20:34.066
What are you talking about?

20:34.608 --> 20:37.861
You knew how confused I was
that I couldn't get pregnant.

20:37.945 --> 20:39.154
I found this.

20:41.865 --> 20:43.200
You been going through my things?

20:43.283 --> 20:46.286
Don't.
Does that even matter?

20:46.370 --> 20:49.164
You've purposely been
taking testosterone injections

20:49.248 --> 20:50.374
so I couldn't get pregnant.

20:50.457 --> 20:52.501
How could you lie to me?!

20:52.709 --> 20:53.961
Madison, listen--

20:54.044 --> 20:56.338
Don't "Madison" me!
I trusted you!

20:56.505 --> 20:58.966
You knew all I wanted to do
was to have kids!

20:59.049 --> 21:01.051
You knew that!

21:01.260 --> 21:05.055
You're right.
I been taking those injections,

21:05.138 --> 21:07.516
'cause I don't want
to have children right now,

21:07.599 --> 21:09.685
and I've told you that
a hundred times,

21:09.768 --> 21:12.479
and you keep pushing it.

21:12.938 --> 21:16.483
I work very hard
to provide this life, Madison.

21:18.527 --> 21:20.737
I pay the bills.

21:20.821 --> 21:23.407
I provide everything.

21:23.782 --> 21:24.908
Is that not good enough?

21:24.992 --> 21:26.535
Yeah, for you,
it's good enough.

21:26.618 --> 21:28.662
What about what I want?
What about me?

21:28.745 --> 21:30.664
What about what I want?!

21:30.789 --> 21:32.791
This is ridiculously selfish of you!

21:32.874 --> 21:34.543
Okay, again,
you need to watch your tone.

21:34.626 --> 21:35.836
You are such a coward.

21:35.919 --> 21:37.045
-You are a coward!
-Okay--

21:37.129 --> 21:38.422
You are a liar!
Don't "okay" me!

21:38.505 --> 21:40.299
-Calm down!
-I'm not gonna calm down!

21:40.382 --> 21:42.175
Do not tell me to calm down!

21:43.176 --> 21:44.720
I do everything for you!

21:44.803 --> 21:47.055
I do everything!
I quit my job for you!

21:47.139 --> 21:49.516
I sit here,
and I cook, and I clean!

21:49.599 --> 21:51.226
I left my father for you!

21:52.769 --> 21:55.564
-I treat you like a king.
-As you should!

21:58.525 --> 21:59.985
As you should!

22:00.068 --> 22:02.112
That is your job!

22:02.946 --> 22:04.489
Be a wife!

22:04.698 --> 22:07.534
As your husband,
I deserve more respect

22:07.617 --> 22:09.369
than you're showing me right now!

22:09.453 --> 22:10.537
You are not.

22:10.620 --> 22:12.039
You are not my husband.

22:12.122 --> 22:13.957
You are a liar.

22:14.624 --> 22:15.459
Respect?

22:15.542 --> 22:18.337
A husband would never lie to his wife!

22:19.296 --> 22:21.965
Your father never would have lied
to your mother like this!

22:24.426 --> 22:26.094
[crying]

22:31.224 --> 22:32.559
Now...

22:33.060 --> 22:36.271
let me make something
perfectly clear to you.

22:36.354 --> 22:38.774
I'm the man of this house.

22:38.857 --> 22:40.776
I make the money.
I make the rules.

22:40.859 --> 22:44.071
I will not be disrespected here.
Do you understand me?

22:46.782 --> 22:48.658
Now...

22:49.326 --> 22:50.744
I'm sorry.

22:50.827 --> 22:51.953
I didn't mean to hit you.

22:52.037 --> 22:53.663
[crying]

22:53.747 --> 22:55.624
But you need to check yourself.

22:57.125 --> 23:00.420
Let's not let that happen again, okay?

23:01.046 --> 23:02.839
It disrupts our household.

23:03.590 --> 23:04.841
And, please,

23:05.092 --> 23:09.554
don't you ever again in life
mention my father.

23:12.307 --> 23:13.517
Now let's get you cleaned up.

23:22.609 --> 23:24.611
[crying]

24:01.189 --> 24:02.649
What?

24:02.732 --> 24:04.776
Nothing.

24:04.860 --> 24:07.571
Just admiring how beautiful you are.

24:08.405 --> 24:10.073
Thank you.

24:11.992 --> 24:14.077
I'm gonna wear
the red dress you picked out.

24:14.661 --> 24:16.163
I love it.

24:19.249 --> 24:22.169
But I think you'd be sexier
with your hair down.

24:22.252 --> 24:24.045
Don't you think?

24:25.130 --> 24:27.174
Oh, are you sure, babe?

24:28.216 --> 24:30.719
I don't know.
I think it looks better up.

24:31.511 --> 24:33.096
[chuckles]

24:33.180 --> 24:35.140
-[overlapping chatter]
-[instrumental playing]

25:06.046 --> 25:08.089
[new instrumental playing]

25:10.759 --> 25:13.762
-Well, I'll see you later.
-Okay, bye. Thank you.

25:19.267 --> 25:21.269
[no audible dialogue]

25:27.108 --> 25:30.028
[tense music plays]

25:32.656 --> 25:33.949
I'm going to bed.

25:35.116 --> 25:39.704
You know, I saw you talking
to my colleague Ryan tonight.

25:39.788 --> 25:41.706
He was being pretty friendly,
don't you think?

25:42.207 --> 25:44.584
I talk to all your colleagues, Michael.

25:45.377 --> 25:47.671
I was socializing for you.

25:48.213 --> 25:50.006
Isn't that why you invite me
to those parties?

25:50.090 --> 25:52.133
Don't play me. It's insulting.

25:53.718 --> 25:56.346
He was practically
undressing you with his eyes.

25:57.389 --> 25:58.348
I didn't notice.

25:58.431 --> 26:00.392
Yes, you did.

26:00.934 --> 26:01.977
You absolutely did.

26:02.060 --> 26:04.980
It was like you guys
knew each other.

26:06.231 --> 26:07.607
Come here.

26:10.986 --> 26:12.821
Come here.

26:20.704 --> 26:22.539
Come on, Michael.

26:23.707 --> 26:25.166
Babe, you're too rough.

26:27.419 --> 26:29.045
Unzip my pants.

26:30.839 --> 26:32.173
Do it.

26:35.051 --> 26:36.553
[zipper unzips]

26:39.097 --> 26:41.141
Michael, stop.

26:41.683 --> 26:43.226
You're being too rough.

26:43.310 --> 26:44.311
[sobs]

26:50.650 --> 26:51.776
[chuckles]

26:53.236 --> 26:54.988
-[chuckles]
-What?

26:57.741 --> 26:58.867
You're pregnant?

26:58.950 --> 27:00.702
I'm pregnant! I'm pregnant!

27:00.785 --> 27:02.954
-[both laugh]
-Oh, my God!

27:03.038 --> 27:05.540
Oh, my God, Madi.
I'm so happy for you.

27:05.623 --> 27:07.250
This is what you've always wanted!

27:08.001 --> 27:10.920
What--Why?
Why aren't you as happy as I am?

27:11.004 --> 27:12.714
Do you think
Michael's gonna be happy?

27:13.298 --> 27:14.924
Girl, are you crazy?

27:15.008 --> 27:17.552
You're having his baby!
You're having his--

27:17.635 --> 27:19.971
Hello. It's your Auntie Chelsea!

27:20.055 --> 27:22.640
Do you hear your auntie in there
screaming?

27:22.724 --> 27:23.933
Ahh!

27:24.017 --> 27:26.311
It's--Oh, my God.

27:26.394 --> 27:28.271
You did it.

27:28.355 --> 27:29.314
Finally.

27:29.397 --> 27:30.774
Finally, you did it.

27:31.816 --> 27:33.068
This is great.

27:36.696 --> 27:38.448
If he found out I was working here

27:38.573 --> 27:39.783
with you, he'd kill me.

27:40.408 --> 27:42.369
I never knew he was so insecure.

27:42.994 --> 27:44.496
He asked me...

27:45.830 --> 27:47.749
if the baby was his.

27:51.086 --> 27:53.088
That's crazy, Madi.

27:55.340 --> 27:58.468
You've only--You've only
been with him, right?

27:59.344 --> 28:01.262
Come on. Of course.

28:04.349 --> 28:06.267
I thought you said
everything was good.

28:06.351 --> 28:07.685
They were.

28:07.769 --> 28:11.314
All of a sudden,
he had a bad day at work,

28:11.398 --> 28:14.192
and I guess
he took it out on me.

28:14.275 --> 28:15.318
Oh, my God.

28:15.402 --> 28:17.070
It's not his fault.

28:17.153 --> 28:18.613
[scoffs]

28:18.696 --> 28:22.200
He's been really stressed.
His job and--

28:22.283 --> 28:23.618
-Stressed?
-and the baby.

28:23.701 --> 28:25.787
That doesn't give him
a reason to hit you.

28:25.870 --> 28:28.373
And while
you're four months pregnant?

28:28.456 --> 28:30.875
You need to stop
making excuses for him

28:30.959 --> 28:32.794
and go to the police.

28:32.877 --> 28:34.879
He's my husband, Chelsea.

28:36.256 --> 28:38.091
I am carrying his child.

28:38.174 --> 28:39.801
I am not gonna go to the police.

28:39.884 --> 28:41.344
I knew it.
I knew he was too perfect.

28:41.428 --> 28:43.221
I knew he was--
Just like my mother said.

28:44.431 --> 28:47.350
What kind of man
hits his pregnant wife

28:47.434 --> 28:50.019
when she's carrying his child?
Who does that?

28:50.103 --> 28:51.438
Stop.

28:51.521 --> 28:54.816
I don't want this to be a bigger deal
than it already is, okay?

28:54.899 --> 28:57.902
Do not--Do not blow this
out of proportion.

28:57.986 --> 28:59.779
Look at your face.

29:01.156 --> 29:02.407
Madison...

29:04.242 --> 29:07.370
we have been best friends
since high school,

29:07.454 --> 29:09.539
and I've always had your back.

29:09.622 --> 29:12.751
You know me, Madi.
You know me.

29:12.834 --> 29:15.420
I'm not just gonna sit back
and do nothing

29:15.503 --> 29:18.590
while this man substitutes his...

29:18.673 --> 29:21.593
-Shh.
-punching bags with your face.

29:21.676 --> 29:23.219
-It's okay.
-If this happens again,

29:23.303 --> 29:25.305
I will go to the police
my damn self.

29:25.388 --> 29:27.098
He won't do it again.

29:28.349 --> 29:29.434
I trust him.

29:29.517 --> 29:30.727
[hip-hop music plays]

29:30.810 --> 29:32.562
♪ Tryin' to mix it all up ♪

29:32.687 --> 29:34.230
♪ Wanna be in control ♪

29:34.314 --> 29:35.857
♪ Yeah, give me more love ♪

29:35.940 --> 29:37.484
♪ I can pick it all up ♪

29:37.567 --> 29:38.943
♪ When I hit it, uh-huh ♪

29:39.027 --> 29:41.070
♪ Why don't you
take it all off? ♪

29:41.154 --> 29:44.199
♪ You know what I mean
when I say you're a rock star ♪

29:44.282 --> 29:45.825
-♪ Rock star ♪
-♪ Queen, girl ♪

29:45.909 --> 29:47.619
-♪ You Prada ♪
-♪ You Prada ♪

29:47.702 --> 29:49.329
♪ I'm a believer ♪

29:49.412 --> 29:52.207
♪ And you know
I'll hold you down... ♪

29:52.290 --> 29:53.291
What's wrong?

29:53.374 --> 29:55.210
[turns off music, engine]

29:55.460 --> 29:57.170
Why are we stopped?
What are you doing?

29:57.253 --> 29:59.339
'Cause I wanna talk!
I wanna know what's wrong with you!

29:59.422 --> 30:01.800
You haven't said anything to me all night.
You ruined dinner.

30:01.883 --> 30:04.093
Now you're not talking to me
on the way home. What's wrong?

30:04.344 --> 30:06.054
What did I ever do to you?

30:07.222 --> 30:08.640
Tell me.

30:09.265 --> 30:11.309
Was I not everything
I promised you I'd be

30:11.392 --> 30:14.020
-when we got married?
-Just stop with the fairy tale.

30:14.103 --> 30:16.564
[mocking] "Oh, was I not
everything I promised I'd be--"

30:16.648 --> 30:18.775
It's life! Get over it!

30:18.858 --> 30:19.943
You never get over it!

30:20.235 --> 30:21.569
You never get over it!

30:21.653 --> 30:23.780
You never let me live it down,
do you?

30:23.863 --> 30:25.782
How many times
do I gotta tell you I'm sorry?

30:25.865 --> 30:27.742
As many times
as you keep doing it!

30:27.826 --> 30:30.578
I'm sorry.
I'm sorry, baby. I'm sorry.

30:30.662 --> 30:32.789
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

30:32.872 --> 30:34.499
I'm really sorry.

30:34.582 --> 30:36.334
-How many times?
-I don't have time for this.

30:36.417 --> 30:38.253
I do not have time for this, Michael!

30:38.336 --> 30:39.921
What are you doing?
What are you doing?

30:40.004 --> 30:41.506
Michael, I don't have time for this!

30:41.589 --> 30:43.007
This is all about you!

30:43.091 --> 30:44.801
Everything is about you!

30:44.884 --> 30:46.302
I'm getting an Uber,

30:46.386 --> 30:48.263
and I'm not gonna be there
when you get home!

30:48.346 --> 30:49.806
You're not--Get--Get--

30:54.394 --> 30:56.104
Have you lost your goddamn mind?

30:56.187 --> 30:58.064
Get back in the car.
You're embarrassing me.

30:58.147 --> 30:59.691
-Stop yelling--
-Shut up. Shut up.

30:59.774 --> 31:01.442
-Don't--
-Shut up.

31:01.609 --> 31:02.610
Get your hand off me.

31:02.777 --> 31:05.280
Get your hand off me.

31:05.446 --> 31:07.198
I've told you about this before.

31:07.282 --> 31:08.950
I cannot live without you.

31:09.033 --> 31:10.827
I will not live with--

31:10.910 --> 31:12.537
-I can't do th--
-Shut up!

31:12.620 --> 31:15.790
Stop threatening me with that!
It's not smart!

31:15.874 --> 31:17.375
Now get back in the car!

31:19.085 --> 31:20.378
-Get in!
-Stop it, Michael!

31:20.461 --> 31:22.630
Get in the freakin' car.

31:39.188 --> 31:41.399
♪ Love has got me over ♪

31:44.777 --> 31:47.906
♪ Got pills on the floor ♪

31:50.825 --> 31:53.578
♪ The pain is running heavy ♪

31:56.623 --> 32:00.043
♪ And covering the sores ♪

32:01.085 --> 32:03.254
♪ No ♪

32:03.338 --> 32:05.340
♪ Covering up the bruises ♪

32:05.423 --> 32:07.759
♪ Ohh ♪

32:09.093 --> 32:12.013
♪ Trying to forget your... ♪

32:12.096 --> 32:13.389
You stop!

32:13.473 --> 32:15.725
-[yelps]
-Every fucking day,

32:15.808 --> 32:17.810
you're doing the same shit!

32:17.894 --> 32:19.354
Stop it!

32:19.479 --> 32:21.481
[crying]

32:24.317 --> 32:29.989
♪ But it hurts ♪

32:37.163 --> 32:39.457
-[crying]
-♪ I wake up ♪

32:39.540 --> 32:43.670
♪ Ohh... ♪

32:43.753 --> 32:47.131
I want you to know that we take
domestic violence very, very seriously.

32:49.300 --> 32:51.719
♪ It's too much ♪

32:53.054 --> 32:57.767
♪ You made me a believer ♪

32:57.850 --> 33:00.019
♪ Believer ♪

33:00.103 --> 33:07.110
♪ I've had enough ♪

33:08.111 --> 33:10.363
I would suggest that she get
a restraining order.

33:10.446 --> 33:12.615
By the time the police arrive,
she could be dead.

33:12.699 --> 33:19.706
♪ I've had enough ♪

33:21.499 --> 33:24.335
Look, I'll give you my card, okay?

33:24.419 --> 33:26.254
And if you need anything
or anything comes up,

33:26.337 --> 33:28.589
just please, uh,
don't hesitate to call, okay?

33:30.800 --> 33:33.177
[fading]
♪ I've had enough ♪

33:34.637 --> 33:36.556
[on TV]
Just feel like I'm just there.

33:36.639 --> 33:38.933
I'm alone.
Everybody down in the world's

33:39.017 --> 33:40.351
-having more fun than me.
-[click]

33:40.435 --> 33:42.311
And I told you
to wear something nice, love...

33:42.395 --> 33:44.856
[Madison]
I'm gonna go to the store.

33:44.939 --> 33:47.233
[on TV] Now exactly
what it is, I don't know.

33:47.316 --> 33:51.738
Is there anything you need me
to get you while I'm out?

33:51.821 --> 33:52.905
[click]

33:52.989 --> 33:54.532
Michael.

33:56.701 --> 34:00.204
Has it really gotten this bad
that you can't even talk to me?

34:00.288 --> 34:02.623
[on TV]
...may have been the worst idea,

34:02.707 --> 34:04.667
and I told him it's stupid.

34:04.751 --> 34:06.669
Fine. I'm gonna go stay at Chelsea's.

34:07.795 --> 34:08.755
[clicks TV off]

34:14.427 --> 34:16.179
You're gonna do what?

34:18.598 --> 34:21.893
Are you--
Are you trying to piss me off?

34:21.976 --> 34:23.853
After all I've done for you,
you're gonna run?

34:23.936 --> 34:26.397
Stop. Stop with that.

34:26.481 --> 34:28.107
It is not about that.

34:29.567 --> 34:31.903
What about love?
What about our wedding vows?

34:31.986 --> 34:34.363
You told me
that you would protect me

34:34.447 --> 34:36.532
from anyone,
anything else out there,

34:36.616 --> 34:38.993
and the main thing
I need protection from is you!

34:42.246 --> 34:44.957
Til death do us part, remember?

34:45.041 --> 34:47.335
Well, kill me then, you pathetic excu--

34:56.761 --> 34:58.429
[vase shatters]

35:00.890 --> 35:02.350
[gasping]

35:13.236 --> 35:14.570
Madison!

35:20.201 --> 35:21.911
Please, don't go!

35:21.994 --> 35:24.163
Madison, no!

35:24.247 --> 35:25.998
No!

35:31.420 --> 35:32.338
Aah!

35:38.845 --> 35:40.263
[gasps]

35:40.346 --> 35:41.472
[tires screech]

35:44.016 --> 35:46.018
[sirens blaring]

35:52.441 --> 35:55.069
[Chelsea crying]

35:55.153 --> 35:57.488
[indistinct P.A. announcement]

35:59.574 --> 36:02.827
Hey. H-Has she improved
since I saw her?

36:02.910 --> 36:05.413
[sighs] She suffered
severe head trauma

36:05.496 --> 36:06.914
from the steering wheel,

36:06.998 --> 36:09.292
which led to internal bleeding
in her brain,

36:09.375 --> 36:13.963
and, um, we tried to do
everything we could to save her,

36:14.046 --> 36:16.424
but unfortunately
she passed during surgery.

36:16.507 --> 36:18.551
[Chelsea] Oh, God.

36:18.634 --> 36:20.636
[sobbing]

36:21.053 --> 36:23.347
Wh-What about the baby?

36:24.765 --> 36:26.350
I'm so sorry, Mr. Roland.

36:26.434 --> 36:29.478
We weren't able
to save the baby either.

36:31.314 --> 36:35.860
Would you, uh,
like to view the body, sir?

36:35.943 --> 36:36.861
No.

36:36.944 --> 36:38.529
[Chelsea] Michael!

36:38.613 --> 36:40.114
Michael.

36:41.157 --> 36:42.658
Michael.

36:44.619 --> 36:46.245
Michael.

39:09.305 --> 39:12.308
[Madison] I was six months
pregnant the day I died.

39:13.768 --> 39:15.728
That same day,
I was able to live again.

39:17.980 --> 39:21.108
[cellphone line rings]

39:21.192 --> 39:23.903
Chelsea, he took the bait.

39:31.410 --> 39:33.204
You sure this is gonna work?

39:33.287 --> 39:35.247
Yes. Within two minutes,
you'll be out.

39:35.331 --> 39:36.874
It'll last long enough

39:36.957 --> 39:39.043
to take you through
to the emergency room.

39:39.126 --> 39:41.212
When you wake up,
you won't remember anything.

40:07.571 --> 40:10.699
Hey. H-Has she improved
since I saw her?

40:12.368 --> 40:15.621
She suffered severe head trauma
from the steering wheel,

40:15.704 --> 40:18.416
which led to internal bleeding
in her brain.

40:20.334 --> 40:22.837
We tried to do everything
we could to save her...

40:30.010 --> 40:32.054
but unfortunately
she passed during surgery.

40:32.138 --> 40:33.514
[Chelsea crying]

40:33.597 --> 40:35.599
What about the baby?

40:50.614 --> 40:52.533
This is crazy. This is crazy.

40:52.616 --> 40:54.285
We could stop.
We don't have to do this.

40:54.368 --> 40:55.995
-No, no, stop.
-It's too much!

40:56.078 --> 40:58.330
-It's too much, Chelsea.
-Stop. It's already done.

40:58.414 --> 41:00.541
-And what if we get caught?
-It's--

41:00.624 --> 41:02.293
It's already done.

41:04.295 --> 41:06.547
This was the right thing to do...

41:08.090 --> 41:12.011
for you, for this baby.

41:14.221 --> 41:15.890
Okay?

41:19.560 --> 41:20.895
I don't wanna go.

41:20.978 --> 41:22.771
Oh, it's gonna be fine.

41:22.855 --> 41:24.648
-It's gonna be fine.
-I don't wanna go.

41:24.732 --> 41:26.275
It's gonna be fine.

41:26.358 --> 41:27.401
Okay.

41:27.485 --> 41:29.153
It's gonna be fine.

41:33.991 --> 41:34.950
Okay, come on.

41:35.910 --> 41:37.119
Come on.

41:50.132 --> 41:53.302
♪ I cannot believe ♪

41:53.385 --> 41:58.265
♪ I found the woman of my dreams ♪

41:58.349 --> 41:59.600
♪ Oh, girl... ♪

41:59.683 --> 42:02.561
It's 3:00 in sunny Silicon Valley

42:02.645 --> 42:05.356
on 96.6, the Heat.

42:05.439 --> 42:07.066
Gonna begin
our midafternoon marathon

42:07.149 --> 42:10.986
with an L.A. classic oldie but goodie.

42:11.070 --> 42:12.279
♪ Yeah ♪

42:12.363 --> 42:13.864
["For the Love of You"
playing]

42:13.948 --> 42:15.658
