42:15.741 --> 42:16.909
[groans]

42:16.992 --> 42:19.495
Hey, are you okay?

42:19.578 --> 42:21.997
Let me help you.

42:22.081 --> 42:26.252
♪ Yeah, ohh ♪

42:27.336 --> 42:29.046
Yeah, I'm fine. I'm fine.

42:29.129 --> 42:30.714
Will you turn that off, please?

42:30.798 --> 42:32.758
-T-The music--
-Okay, I got you.

42:32.841 --> 42:34.176
♪ Drifting on a memory ♪

42:35.177 --> 42:36.512
[changes station]

42:36.595 --> 42:39.723
♪ Can't wait to see you again ♪

42:39.807 --> 42:42.268
Okay, Kate,
I'm getting out of here.

42:42.351 --> 42:43.352
-You leaving?
-You got this?

42:43.435 --> 42:44.353
-I got it.
-All right.

42:44.436 --> 42:45.771
Don't forget to cut off the lights...

42:45.854 --> 42:46.939
[together]
and set the alarm.

42:47.022 --> 42:48.482
-You got it.
-Have a good night.

42:56.615 --> 42:59.702
♪ She just said, "Stay..." ♪

43:01.954 --> 43:03.205
[both laugh]

43:03.289 --> 43:04.373
[Madison] Hi!

43:05.833 --> 43:06.750
Hey.

43:06.834 --> 43:09.878
-Oh, my God.
-Ohh!

43:09.962 --> 43:11.505
Oh, what a surprise.

43:11.589 --> 43:13.299
Oh, long.

43:13.382 --> 43:14.592
Let's sit.

43:14.675 --> 43:16.844
Did anyone follow you?

43:16.927 --> 43:19.680
[scoffs]
Come on, Madi. You--

43:19.763 --> 43:21.807
I mean Kate.

43:21.890 --> 43:23.183
[chuckles]

43:23.267 --> 43:24.977
I'm smarter than that.

43:25.060 --> 43:26.312
I know. I'm sorry.

43:26.395 --> 43:28.230
Just a little nervous still.

43:28.314 --> 43:29.773
Yeah.

43:29.857 --> 43:31.525
Sometimes I can feel him,
you know?

43:32.526 --> 43:34.403
That's okay. I get it.

43:36.739 --> 43:38.073
Thank you.

43:38.157 --> 43:41.243
This has been risky,
to say the least.

43:41.327 --> 43:44.038
Mm. I got your back, girl.

43:44.121 --> 43:45.122
Thanks.

43:45.205 --> 43:47.416
You know what I don't get?

43:47.499 --> 43:49.627
-What?
-How you chose the name Kate.

43:49.710 --> 43:52.087
[laughs] I hate that name!

43:52.171 --> 43:53.797
-Why?
-Well, I don't know.

43:53.881 --> 43:56.467
Why didn't you go something exotic
like Paris or...

43:56.550 --> 43:58.636
[laughs]

43:58.719 --> 44:00.554
No, not doing Paris.

44:00.638 --> 44:02.514
I've always wanted to go to Paris.

44:02.598 --> 44:03.599
Could do that.

44:03.682 --> 44:05.392
Well...

44:07.770 --> 44:13.317
with all this money,
you can take us both to Paris.

44:13.400 --> 44:14.610
Oh.

44:14.693 --> 44:16.070
-Whoa.
-[laughing]

44:16.153 --> 44:18.530
I am so glad
I made you the beneficiary.

44:18.614 --> 44:20.074
It was a genius idea.

44:20.157 --> 44:22.368
So tell me everything.

44:22.451 --> 44:24.370
I wanna know.
I wanna know about everything.

44:24.453 --> 44:27.915
How's your new house,
new environment?

44:27.998 --> 44:30.125
I mean, you must be going crazy here...

44:30.209 --> 44:31.669
around no one you know.

44:31.752 --> 44:35.673
Honestly, Chelsea,
I feel so free.

44:35.756 --> 44:38.509
I mean, I love my house.
It's perfect.

44:38.592 --> 44:40.928
I feel so safe away from him,

44:41.011 --> 44:43.514
and I finally got my black piano.

44:43.597 --> 44:46.350
Ah! You've always wanted a black piano.

44:46.433 --> 44:47.351
I know.

44:47.434 --> 44:48.560
How's the little one?

44:48.644 --> 44:51.146
He will be playing it, too.

44:51.230 --> 44:52.439
He?

44:52.523 --> 44:53.774
-He.
-It's a he?

44:53.857 --> 44:55.859
-Yes.
-It's a boy?

44:55.943 --> 44:58.362
♪ What's up? How do you do? ♪

44:58.445 --> 45:02.241
♪ It's been a few minutes
since I've been watching you ♪

45:02.324 --> 45:04.326
-♪ Do what you do ♪
-Yes.

45:04.410 --> 45:06.995
♪ No, I can't lie,
I'm feeling you ♪

45:07.079 --> 45:11.041
♪ But something about you ♪

45:11.125 --> 45:14.670
♪ That I can't figure it out ♪

45:14.753 --> 45:17.297
♪ No doubt,
it's what it's all about ♪

45:17.381 --> 45:18.715
♪ The mysteries ♪

45:18.799 --> 45:21.093
♪ The uncertainties,
yeah, yeah ♪

45:21.176 --> 45:23.303
♪ It's real,
just wanna chill ♪

45:23.387 --> 45:24.847
♪ Get to know you maybe ♪

45:24.930 --> 45:27.891
♪ Even have a little meal,
just chill ♪

45:27.975 --> 45:29.935
♪ You tell your friends ♪

45:30.018 --> 45:31.520
♪ I'll tell my friends ♪

45:31.603 --> 45:34.565
♪ Nothing serious, just chill ♪

45:46.869 --> 45:48.871
[new song playing]

45:57.671 --> 45:59.756
♪ Billy Ray
was a preacher's son ♪

45:59.840 --> 46:02.634
♪ And when his daddy
would visit, he'd come along ♪

46:02.718 --> 46:04.720
♪ When they gathered round
and started talking ♪

46:04.803 --> 46:06.138
[knock on door]

46:06.221 --> 46:08.474
♪ That's when Billy
would take me walking ♪

46:08.557 --> 46:11.143
♪ Through the backyard,
we'd go walking ♪

46:11.226 --> 46:13.687
[knocking again]
♪ Then he'd look into my eyes ♪

46:13.770 --> 46:16.064
♪ Lord knows, to my surprise ♪

46:16.148 --> 46:19.067
♪ The only one
who could ever reach me ♪

46:19.151 --> 46:21.195
♪ Was the son
of a preacher man ♪

46:21.278 --> 46:22.404
♪ The only boy... ♪

46:22.488 --> 46:24.198
Hi. Oh, um, hi.

46:24.281 --> 46:27.951
Uh, I'm Alex,
and this is my daughter Rachel.

46:28.035 --> 46:29.745
-Introduce yourself.
-Hi.

46:29.828 --> 46:32.748
My name is Rachel Stone,
and I'm six years old.

46:32.831 --> 46:34.041
How old are you?

46:34.124 --> 46:35.459
-[laughs]
-No. "How are you"?

46:35.542 --> 46:37.294
I didn't ask her to say that,
"How old?"

46:37.377 --> 46:39.296
-Wow, she is adorable.
-Yeah.

46:39.379 --> 46:42.090
Rachel, a woman never tells her age.

46:42.174 --> 46:43.592
We, uh--Sorry about that.

46:43.675 --> 46:45.052
We're--We're next door.

46:45.135 --> 46:47.638
Uh, Rachel's school
is doing a toy drive,

46:47.721 --> 46:49.806
so we're going around
to all the neighbors

46:49.890 --> 46:52.935
and asking for, uh, donations,
contributions.

46:54.019 --> 46:54.937
Hi. I'm Kate.

46:55.020 --> 46:56.772
Nice to meet you, Kate.

46:56.855 --> 46:57.898
One second, okay?

46:57.981 --> 46:59.274
Okay.

46:59.358 --> 47:01.235
♪ ...boy that could
ever teach me ♪

47:01.318 --> 47:03.070
♪ Was the son
of a preacher man... ♪

47:03.153 --> 47:05.280
Oh, she looks--
She seems nice, right?

47:05.364 --> 47:06.782
-Mm-hmm.
-Yeah.

47:06.865 --> 47:08.992
-Right next door.
-The nice, nice neighbor.

47:09.076 --> 47:10.452
Say what? Hey.

47:10.536 --> 47:11.995
-I hope this helps.
-Oh!

47:12.079 --> 47:13.580
[laughs]

47:13.664 --> 47:14.748
Thank you.

47:14.831 --> 47:15.999
You're welcome.

47:16.083 --> 47:17.960
Anything for the kids, anything,

47:18.043 --> 47:20.462
especially one as cute as you.

47:20.546 --> 47:21.880
Thank you. We appreciate it.

47:21.964 --> 47:23.840
Um, well, congratulations.

47:23.924 --> 47:26.301
You guys must be excited,
you and your husband.

47:26.385 --> 47:29.471
-Husband? You said--You said, "Husband."
-Oh, I'm sorry, no. I didn't--

47:29.555 --> 47:31.765
-Who said anything about a husband?
-I'm sorry. I just, uh--

47:31.848 --> 47:33.141
I assumed a pretty girl--

47:33.225 --> 47:34.351
Okay, sorry about that.

47:34.434 --> 47:35.477
That's my bad.

47:35.561 --> 47:36.770
All right, thank you.

47:36.853 --> 47:38.522
-Good luck.
-Thank you.

47:38.605 --> 47:39.898
Uh, nice--
nice to meet you, too, Alex.

47:39.982 --> 47:41.858
Yes. You need any help
around the neighborhood,

47:41.942 --> 47:43.360
-I'm right next door.
-Okay.

47:43.443 --> 47:44.361
Thank you.

47:44.444 --> 47:46.029
♪ Yes, he was ♪

47:46.113 --> 47:48.198
♪ The only one
who could ever reach me ♪

47:48.282 --> 47:51.159
♪ He was the sweet-talking
son of a preacher man ♪

47:51.243 --> 47:53.745
♪ The only boy
who could ever teach me ♪

47:53.829 --> 47:56.164
♪ Ah, I kissed him,
the son of a preacher man ♪

47:56.248 --> 47:58.125
♪ The only one
who could ever... ♪

47:58.208 --> 48:00.210
[heavy metal playing]

48:19.646 --> 48:21.648
[muted heavy metal playing]

48:29.906 --> 48:31.908
[heavy metal blaring]

48:42.544 --> 48:43.795
[Madison] Excuse me.

48:45.422 --> 48:47.007
[muted heavy metal playing]

48:47.090 --> 48:49.092
Excuse me!

48:49.176 --> 48:50.927
-[clears throat]
-Excuse me!

48:51.011 --> 48:52.471
Oh, my--[laughs]

48:52.554 --> 48:54.056
-[heavy metal blaring]
-You startled me!

48:54.139 --> 48:56.016
-You don't have to yell.
-Oh. Sorry.

48:56.099 --> 48:57.809
You startled me.
Yeah, I'm, uh--

48:57.893 --> 48:59.311
It's my bad. I was--

48:59.394 --> 49:01.938
I'm into my music in my yard,
keeping busy.

49:02.022 --> 49:03.523
Well, Mr. Busy,

49:03.607 --> 49:07.611
I noticed that you were
stealing my lemons from my tree.

49:07.694 --> 49:09.112
Oh, okay.

49:09.196 --> 49:12.658
Uh, well, I apologize,
Miss Lemon Tree Police,

49:12.741 --> 49:16.078
uh, but your lemons
were falling over into my yard,

49:16.161 --> 49:17.621
so I gotta scoop 'em up,

49:17.704 --> 49:19.873
so I don't know
what you think about that.

49:19.956 --> 49:22.584
Well, I could call the police
and report you for trespassing,

49:22.668 --> 49:24.544
so what you gonna do about that?

49:24.628 --> 49:27.381
Hmm. Well, I could say

49:27.464 --> 49:29.466
that you're standing
on my property right now,

49:29.549 --> 49:31.593
so who really is the trespasser?

49:31.677 --> 49:32.844
Touché.

49:32.928 --> 49:34.221
[laughs]

49:34.304 --> 49:36.723
I admit I was borrowing your lemons,

49:36.807 --> 49:38.266
but for good reason.

49:38.350 --> 49:41.186
Um, see, I make--
I make a mean lemon meringue pie.

49:41.269 --> 49:42.896
-Really?
-Mm-hmm.

49:43.605 --> 49:44.731
With my lemons.

49:45.357 --> 49:47.025
Yes, with your lemons.

49:47.109 --> 49:48.568
So you cook?

49:48.652 --> 49:50.487
No, I don't cook.

49:50.570 --> 49:52.989
I--I throw down.
That's--That's what I do.

49:53.073 --> 49:54.449
-Really?
-Yes, yes.

49:54.533 --> 49:56.076
As a matter of fact...

49:57.160 --> 49:58.537
this may seem weird,

49:58.620 --> 50:01.498
but I'm making lemon meringue pie
tonight for my daughter,

50:01.581 --> 50:04.918
a-and since I'll be using
your borrowed lemons,

50:05.001 --> 50:07.587
-why don't you--why don't you join us?
-No, I don't think so.

50:07.671 --> 50:10.924
No? All right.
Well, think about it?

50:11.007 --> 50:12.217
I'll think about it.

50:12.300 --> 50:14.803
-Okay.
-Alex, the lemon thief.

50:14.886 --> 50:16.596
Okay. [laughs]

50:16.680 --> 50:19.141
Okay, Kate, Miss Trespasser.

50:20.475 --> 50:21.810
Heh.

50:21.893 --> 50:23.437
Think about it!

50:35.949 --> 50:36.992
Hey!

50:38.034 --> 50:39.453
What's up?

50:39.536 --> 50:41.997
You can't have lemon meringue pie
without the ice cream.

50:42.080 --> 50:44.833
[laughs] Come in.

50:45.959 --> 50:46.918
Is that enough?

50:47.002 --> 50:48.253
I think so.

50:48.336 --> 50:50.547
[hip-hop playing]

50:52.007 --> 50:54.760
♪ Open up the champagne, pop ♪

50:54.843 --> 50:57.512
♪ It's my house,
come on, turn it up ♪

50:57.596 --> 51:01.099
♪ Hear a knock on the door,
and the night begins ♪

51:02.809 --> 51:06.104
♪ 'Cause we done this before,
so you come on in ♪

51:07.814 --> 51:11.401
♪ Make yourself at my home,
tell me where you been ♪

51:13.278 --> 51:16.948
♪ Pour yourself something cold,
baby, cheers to this ♪

51:17.032 --> 51:19.284
♪ Sometimes you gotta stay in ♪

51:19.367 --> 51:22.162
♪ And you know where I live ♪

51:22.245 --> 51:24.372
♪ Yeah, you know what we is ♪

51:24.456 --> 51:27.125
♪ Sometimes you gotta stay in, in ♪

51:27.209 --> 51:29.461
♪ Welcome to my house ♪

51:29.544 --> 51:31.797
♪ Baby, take control now ♪

51:31.880 --> 51:34.341
♪ We can't even slow down ♪

51:34.424 --> 51:37.052
♪ We don't have to go out ♪

51:37.135 --> 51:39.638
♪ Welcome to my house ♪

51:39.721 --> 51:41.973
♪ Play that music too loud ♪

51:42.057 --> 51:44.559
♪ Show me what you do now ♪

51:44.643 --> 51:47.395
♪ We don't have to go out ♪

51:50.023 --> 51:52.859
♪ Unh, welcome to my house ♪

51:55.821 --> 51:58.824
♪ Welcome to my house ♪

51:58.907 --> 52:02.327
♪ Morning comes, and you know
that you wanna stay ♪

52:03.328 --> 52:05.121
♪ Close the blinds ♪

52:05.205 --> 52:09.000
♪ Let's pretend
that the time has changed ♪

52:09.084 --> 52:10.669
♪ Keep our clothes
on the floor ♪

52:10.752 --> 52:12.420
♪ Open up champagne ♪

52:14.172 --> 52:17.050
♪ Let's continue tonight,
come on, celebrate ♪

52:17.133 --> 52:20.470
-♪ That's how we do ♪
-♪ So welcome to my house ♪

52:20.554 --> 52:22.848
-♪ Play that music too loud ♪
-♪ Turn it up ♪

52:22.931 --> 52:25.517
♪ Show me what you do now ♪

52:25.600 --> 52:27.644
♪ We don't have to go out ♪

52:27.727 --> 52:29.980
♪ Go out, it's my house ♪

52:30.063 --> 52:31.982
[Alex laughs]

52:32.065 --> 52:35.026
Well, Chelsea gives her approval.

52:35.110 --> 52:36.278
She's a handful.

52:36.361 --> 52:38.405
Yeah, she is.

52:39.614 --> 52:41.324
-She just left.
-Ah, boy.

52:41.408 --> 52:42.450
Where's Rachel?

52:42.534 --> 52:45.579
Oh, she's asleep. She's out.

52:45.662 --> 52:46.788
Passed out, huh?

52:46.872 --> 52:49.207
Yep. Look at the stars.

52:50.917 --> 52:52.335
Yeah.

52:52.419 --> 52:53.753
-I meant to ask you something.
-Hmm?

52:53.837 --> 52:55.839
Why just you and Rachel?

52:56.840 --> 52:58.758
You divorced?

52:58.842 --> 53:01.094
No. No.

53:01.177 --> 53:05.974
Uh, my wife passed on
when she was delivering Rachel.

53:06.057 --> 53:07.809
-I'm so sorry.
-That's okay.

53:07.893 --> 53:09.978
I mean,
I feel like such a jerk.

53:10.061 --> 53:11.813
-I did not mean to pry.
-It's all right.

53:11.897 --> 53:14.524
It's all right. It's good
to talk about it, healthy,

53:14.608 --> 53:16.443
get it out.

53:16.526 --> 53:17.861
I mean, obviously, you know,

53:17.944 --> 53:19.237
there are good days
and bad days,

53:19.321 --> 53:23.199
but, uh, you know, when she--

53:24.367 --> 53:26.703
I was blessed with Rachel, so...

53:28.163 --> 53:30.957
[chuckles]
She'd be proud.

53:31.041 --> 53:32.834
Uh, enough about me.

53:32.918 --> 53:34.878
What's up with you, though?
No ring?

53:34.961 --> 53:37.047
Walking around
good and pregnant.

53:37.130 --> 53:40.675
I saw you yesterday
at the--the Farmhouse.

53:40.759 --> 53:44.220
I called your name,
but you must have not heard me.

53:44.304 --> 53:49.601
I must have--I go deaf sometimes
when I shop, so...

53:49.684 --> 53:51.811
Okay. [chuckles]

53:51.895 --> 53:55.398
It almost seemed
like your name wasn't Kate.

53:55.482 --> 53:57.442
Well, it is.

53:57.525 --> 53:58.735
Okay.

54:00.028 --> 54:01.821
I mean, it's okay if it isn't...

54:03.573 --> 54:04.741
you know?

54:05.742 --> 54:07.327
I won't tell.

54:12.165 --> 54:13.792
Is it Laquanda?

54:13.875 --> 54:15.335
[scoffs]

54:15.418 --> 54:16.711
[laughs]

54:16.795 --> 54:19.214
Hanging out with Chelsea too long.

54:22.550 --> 54:24.344
Why did you change it?

54:28.932 --> 54:31.726
I married the wrong man.

54:32.018 --> 54:34.938
He was abusive...

54:35.021 --> 54:37.732
mentally, physically.

54:39.859 --> 54:42.529
He was the perfect guy until...

54:43.697 --> 54:45.407
one day, he wasn't.

54:45.490 --> 54:46.700
Okay, I'm sorry. I didn't--

54:46.783 --> 54:49.744
-You don't have to talk about this.
-No, it's okay.

54:49.828 --> 54:53.581
Like you said,
good to talk about it, right?

54:57.711 --> 54:59.170
It just came out of nowhere.

54:59.254 --> 55:00.588
He just snapped.

55:01.965 --> 55:06.553
It was like I never knew him,
like I married a stranger.

55:08.513 --> 55:12.308
I asked myself
how could this man

55:12.392 --> 55:15.895
ever put his hands on the woman
he said he loved so much?

55:15.979 --> 55:16.980
Hmm.

55:19.566 --> 55:21.943
God, those nightmares,
those memories,

55:22.027 --> 55:24.654
they still haunt me,
nightmares, you know.

55:27.741 --> 55:29.242
I'm sorry.

55:33.621 --> 55:35.331
I'm sorry.

55:45.425 --> 55:47.052
Just stop.

55:47.135 --> 55:48.595
What?

55:50.889 --> 55:53.683
Stop staring at me.

55:56.686 --> 55:58.605
I can't help it.

56:04.027 --> 56:05.153
I'm sorry.

56:05.236 --> 56:06.905
-Uh, I'm sorry.
-I am sorry.

56:06.988 --> 56:08.490
-No, it's okay.
-I'm sorry. I can't--

56:08.573 --> 56:09.866
-That was--
-I just--

56:09.949 --> 56:11.284
-I get it. I know.
-Okay.

56:11.367 --> 56:13.703
I didn't--
Do you want me to get the--

56:13.787 --> 56:15.371
-No, it's okay. Okay.
-Okay.

56:16.372 --> 56:19.626
I-I'm sorry.

56:29.636 --> 56:31.888
Mr. Roland, you have a call,
line one.

56:31.971 --> 56:33.640
Uh, could you take a message,
please?

56:33.723 --> 56:36.309
They said it's regarding your wife.

56:36.392 --> 56:38.228
Okay. Thank you.

56:39.813 --> 56:41.189
This is Mr. Roland.

56:41.272 --> 56:43.024
Hello, Mr. Roland.
This is Brenda Walsh

56:43.108 --> 56:45.235
in the Finance Department
over at McKinley Medical.

56:45.318 --> 56:47.821
I'm trying to reach your wife,
Madison.

56:47.904 --> 56:49.906
She never picked up
her last paycheck,

56:49.989 --> 56:51.324
and we've been trying to reach her,

56:51.407 --> 56:54.077
but the number we have on file for her
seems to have changed.

56:54.160 --> 56:56.621
Um, I'm--I'm sorry.

56:56.704 --> 56:58.665
I don't know what you're--
what you're talking about.

56:58.748 --> 57:00.041
Paycheck?

57:00.125 --> 57:02.252
It's her final paycheck.

57:02.335 --> 57:04.587
When she quit a few months ago,
she never collected it.

57:04.671 --> 57:08.049
Huh. There must be
some kind of mistake.

57:08.133 --> 57:10.844
My wife never worked
at your hospital, ma'am.

57:10.927 --> 57:12.846
Her best friend Chelsea did.

57:12.929 --> 57:14.514
Maybe you have them confused?

57:14.597 --> 57:16.474
I'm sure she did.

57:16.558 --> 57:20.228
Uh, says here in our records
that your wife worked mornings

57:20.311 --> 57:22.814
two days a week,
Wednesdays and Thursdays.

57:22.897 --> 57:26.067
There's a mistake. My wife
would go for her morning runs

57:26.151 --> 57:28.486
on Wednesdays
and Thursday mornings.

57:28.570 --> 57:31.072
That is so strange.
It clearly says

57:31.156 --> 57:33.199
that Madison Roland
was an employee.

57:34.742 --> 57:37.203
Okay.
I don't know what's going on,

57:37.287 --> 57:40.206
but my wife won't be picking up
any paychecks anytime soon.

57:40.290 --> 57:42.125
She died a few months ago.

57:42.208 --> 57:44.919
Um, are you new to the hospital?

57:45.003 --> 57:49.090
No, sir. I-I'm not.
I've been here 10 years. Why?

57:49.174 --> 57:50.925
Well, she died in your hospital,

57:51.009 --> 57:53.511
and I would think that you would
have record of that on file.

57:53.595 --> 57:55.680
Hold on, Mr. Roland.

58:00.560 --> 58:03.521
Okay, I do have here in our database

58:03.605 --> 58:06.107
that Madison Roland was admitted
into the emergency room

58:06.191 --> 58:10.570
at 10:45 p.m., March 21,
due to a car accident.

58:12.071 --> 58:13.781
That is so strange.

58:13.865 --> 58:17.035
It doesn't have her time of death.

58:17.118 --> 58:21.831
It says that she was checked out
that same night at 11:37 p.m.

58:38.306 --> 58:41.559
[over P.A.]
Dr. Forrest, dial 118 please?

58:41.643 --> 58:43.686
Dr. Forrest, please dial--

58:43.770 --> 58:46.064
Excuse me. I'm looking
for a Dr. Foster, please?

58:46.147 --> 58:48.399
I apologize, sir.
We don't have a Dr. Foster here.

58:48.483 --> 58:50.818
Uh, can you check?
I'm sure I've seen him here before.

58:50.902 --> 58:52.654
Sir, it's my job
to know all the doctors here.

58:52.737 --> 58:55.198
I would know if there was a Dr. Foster,
which we don't.

58:55.281 --> 58:58.785
Okay. I'm sure you're quite capable,
but can you please check?

58:58.868 --> 59:01.412
Maybe he's on a different wing or side
or whatever you guys say.

59:01.496 --> 59:02.914
Maybe you're at the wrong hospital.

59:02.997 --> 59:05.458
There's actually another hospital
couple blocks from here.

59:05.542 --> 59:07.961
-You could check there.
-Okay, I know where...

59:10.630 --> 59:12.465
[sighs]

59:13.925 --> 59:16.970
I'm sorry.
It's been a long day.

59:17.053 --> 59:19.764
My name is Michael Roland.
My wife is Madison Roland.

59:19.847 --> 59:23.643
-She was checked out March 21.
-Oh, she was?

59:23.726 --> 59:26.396
I--Yeah, I just needed
a copy of her records.

59:26.479 --> 59:28.606
Uh, she's pregnant.
I need 'em for her new doctor.

59:28.690 --> 59:30.066
We just moved upstate.

59:30.149 --> 59:32.360
She was checked out March 21.

59:32.443 --> 59:34.279
Excuse me, Heather.
Do you mind checking to see

59:34.362 --> 59:37.740
if we have a, um, file
for Madison Roland, please?

59:37.824 --> 59:38.825
Sure.

59:40.910 --> 59:42.078
What?

59:42.161 --> 59:43.454
How's your day going?

59:43.538 --> 59:44.831
-Swell, thank you.
-Good.

59:44.914 --> 59:46.374
-How 'bout you?
-Uh, like I said, long.

59:46.457 --> 59:47.875
Got it.

59:47.959 --> 59:51.379
Sir, do you mind if I get
some I.D., please?

59:54.924 --> 59:56.384
Thank you.

59:58.052 --> 1:00:03.933
Okay, and she left this the night,
uh, she left.

1:00:04.017 --> 1:00:05.393
All right.

1:00:05.476 --> 1:00:06.978
Can I see the file, please?

1:00:07.061 --> 1:00:08.563
Sir, whatever information you need,

1:00:08.646 --> 1:00:10.315
I'm happy to fax it over
to the doctor.

1:00:10.398 --> 1:00:11.608
Okay, but I'm here.
It's my wife.

1:00:11.691 --> 1:00:13.192
We're having a child.
I can just take it--

1:00:13.276 --> 1:00:14.652
Sir, I can't give you the file,

1:00:14.736 --> 1:00:17.155
but I'm happy to fax it over
to your doctor for you.

1:00:17.238 --> 1:00:18.323
[sighs]

1:00:18.406 --> 1:00:22.076
Ever notice how everything
has to be difficult?

1:00:23.244 --> 1:00:25.246
It's a beautiful necklace.

1:00:29.167 --> 1:00:30.668
Thank you.

1:00:34.631 --> 1:00:37.717
♪ I can tell right now
that you're happy to see me... ♪

1:00:40.553 --> 1:00:41.804
There you go.

1:00:41.888 --> 1:00:43.473
There you go.
Whenever you're ready, okay?

1:00:43.556 --> 1:00:44.515
Thank you.

1:00:44.599 --> 1:00:46.184
[cellphone rings]

1:00:48.102 --> 1:00:49.312
[ring]

1:00:49.395 --> 1:00:51.105
Hey, Chels.

1:00:53.149 --> 1:00:56.194
Okay, I'm on my way. Yeah.

1:00:56.277 --> 1:00:58.154
-Hey, Amanda.
-Hey.

1:00:58.237 --> 1:00:59.656
I--I have a family emergency.

1:00:59.739 --> 1:01:01.115
Will you take care of everything?

1:01:01.199 --> 1:01:02.825
Yeah. Is everything okay?

1:01:02.909 --> 1:01:04.661
Yeah, I think so.

1:01:04.744 --> 1:01:05.995
All right, well, go.
I got this.

1:01:06.079 --> 1:01:07.747
-Okay. Thank you.
-Get out of here.

1:01:24.347 --> 1:01:26.015
Hi, Daddy.

1:01:37.110 --> 1:01:42.490
Doctors say I don't have much time left.

1:01:46.202 --> 1:01:48.996
I'm so sorry I wasn't here.

1:01:51.290 --> 1:01:54.335
It's okay, princess.

1:01:54.419 --> 1:01:57.004
I know you're really busy.

1:02:02.802 --> 1:02:04.679
I'm here now.

1:02:20.069 --> 1:02:21.654
-Hello, sir.
-Hi. Hi.

1:02:21.738 --> 1:02:23.781
-How can I help you?
-Uh, my name's Michael Roland.

1:02:23.865 --> 1:02:25.700
I'm here to see my father-in-law,
John Harris.

1:02:25.783 --> 1:02:27.702
Okay. Let me check on that.

1:02:27.785 --> 1:02:30.997
You know, you should
give your mother a call.

1:02:31.080 --> 1:02:33.708
It'd make her so happy.

1:02:39.297 --> 1:02:42.925
I don't wanna talk
about Mommy right now, okay.

1:02:43.009 --> 1:02:45.178
When's the last time
you talked to her?

1:02:46.888 --> 1:02:48.806
Long time.

1:02:53.060 --> 1:02:56.439
[sighs]
You're gonna be a granddaddy.

1:02:59.025 --> 1:03:01.903
Wow.

1:03:01.986 --> 1:03:04.363
Okay, it looks like he's
been moved to the west wing,

1:03:04.447 --> 1:03:06.741
due to a stroke he had
a couple of days ago.

1:03:06.824 --> 1:03:07.784
Really?

1:03:07.867 --> 1:03:10.369
Why don't you stay a while?

1:03:11.746 --> 1:03:16.417
You know, I don't get
many visitors lately.

1:03:24.801 --> 1:03:26.469
If you make a right
down this hallway,

1:03:26.552 --> 1:03:28.429
you'll find him in room 13.

1:03:28.513 --> 1:03:29.555
-Down here?
-Right. That way.

1:03:29.639 --> 1:03:30.807
-Thank you.
-You're welcome.

1:03:31.015 --> 1:03:33.100
I love you.

1:03:36.437 --> 1:03:38.397
I love you, too.

1:03:50.952 --> 1:03:54.831
Hey, princess. That you again?

1:03:56.749 --> 1:03:57.875
No, Pops.

1:03:59.335 --> 1:04:02.088
It's me, Michael.

1:04:02.755 --> 1:04:04.924
[John] Hey. How you doing?

1:04:05.007 --> 1:04:08.094
I'm good. I'm good.
Came to check you out.

1:04:08.177 --> 1:04:10.763
I'm good. I'm glad to see you.

1:04:10.847 --> 1:04:14.809
You and--
You came together with Madison?

1:04:16.561 --> 1:04:17.562
What did you say?

1:04:18.437 --> 1:04:22.191
Madison.
She was right here talking to me.

1:04:25.194 --> 1:04:28.447
Nah, it was hard on all of us
when we lost her, Pops.

1:04:30.199 --> 1:04:32.201
What do you mean, "lost"?

1:04:33.911 --> 1:04:36.330
I mean she died.

1:04:37.665 --> 1:04:40.376
Madison's not dead.

1:04:40.459 --> 1:04:43.921
Madison was just right here
just talking with me.

1:04:44.005 --> 1:04:46.841
Her mother's coming to see me, too.

1:04:48.426 --> 1:04:51.888
We're gonna have ourselves a picnic,

1:04:51.971 --> 1:04:55.683
just all of us together.

1:04:55.766 --> 1:04:57.768
You should stay for the picnic.

1:04:59.061 --> 1:05:01.647
Mary would love to see you,

1:05:01.731 --> 1:05:04.859
just like we used to, like old times.

1:05:04.942 --> 1:05:06.319
Sorry, Pops.

1:05:09.196 --> 1:05:11.699
I'm not gonna be able to stay.

1:05:14.493 --> 1:05:16.287
But I'll come back.

1:05:16.370 --> 1:05:17.997
I'll see you again.

1:05:19.999 --> 1:05:21.959
[heavy metal playing]

1:05:23.836 --> 1:05:25.129
Hey, you!

1:05:26.797 --> 1:05:28.174
-Hey!
-Hey, you.

1:05:28.257 --> 1:05:29.508
What's up?

1:05:29.592 --> 1:05:31.469
Alex, the lemon thief.

1:05:31.552 --> 1:05:32.470
Say what?

1:05:32.553 --> 1:05:34.472
Alex, the lemon thief.

1:05:34.555 --> 1:05:36.432
Ah, Kate the trespasser.

1:05:36.515 --> 1:05:37.516
[laughs]

1:05:39.018 --> 1:05:40.102
About last night--

1:05:40.186 --> 1:05:41.395
Ah, please, no. You don't--

1:05:41.520 --> 1:05:43.356
It's all good, all right?

1:05:43.439 --> 1:05:45.691
Sorry it was so awkward.
I get it.

1:05:45.775 --> 1:05:49.278
Um, I think you should know
I like you,

1:05:49.362 --> 1:05:52.365
so I just hope
you don't treat this situation,

1:05:52.448 --> 1:05:54.700
you know, like the old ones.

1:05:54.784 --> 1:05:56.243
No, I don't. Trust me.

1:05:56.327 --> 1:05:59.580
Um, so I wanted to say I'm sorry,

1:05:59.664 --> 1:06:04.669
and it's just this, us,
it's kind of scary, you know?

1:06:04.752 --> 1:06:06.671
Yeah. I'm scared, too.
I'm still healing.

1:06:06.754 --> 1:06:08.255
[laughs]

1:06:08.339 --> 1:06:11.092
Uh, what do you say we just
take it one step at a time?

1:06:11.175 --> 1:06:12.593
Yeah. Yes. I'd like that.

1:06:12.677 --> 1:06:13.761
Cool. All right. Me, too.

1:06:13.844 --> 1:06:15.054
I'm glad we're still talking,

1:06:15.137 --> 1:06:17.932
'cause, uh,
Rachel misses you so.

1:06:18.015 --> 1:06:19.225
It's good.

1:06:19.308 --> 1:06:20.768
You're gonna put this on Rachel?

1:06:20.851 --> 1:06:23.854
-Say what?
-You didn't miss me?

1:06:23.938 --> 1:06:25.272
No. It's only been a day,

1:06:25.356 --> 1:06:26.941
-so I don't know--
-Little bit?

1:06:27.024 --> 1:06:28.401
-No, no.
-Okay.

1:06:28.484 --> 1:06:29.944
-A little bit.
-[both laugh]

1:06:30.027 --> 1:06:31.362
-Thank you.
-I did.

1:06:31.445 --> 1:06:32.488
All right, cool.

1:06:32.571 --> 1:06:34.657
-Good talk. Good talk.
-Yes.

1:06:34.740 --> 1:06:36.325
-Thank you.
-All right. [laughs]

1:06:36.409 --> 1:06:39.704
-Back to work, busy man.
-Yes, watering the lawn.

1:06:39.787 --> 1:06:41.539
-[Madison laughing]
-[Alex groans]

1:06:44.125 --> 1:06:47.294
[Rob] And what even makes you
think she's still alive?

1:06:47.378 --> 1:06:50.089
Well, I got a call from the hospital

1:06:50.172 --> 1:06:54.552
saying that she had failed
to pick up her last paycheck,

1:06:55.136 --> 1:07:00.558
and when I pressed them on it,
they said she was checked in,

1:07:00.641 --> 1:07:02.893
and then she was checked out.

1:07:02.977 --> 1:07:05.479
They didn't have
any record of her dying.

1:07:05.563 --> 1:07:07.189
But you did see the body, right?

1:07:07.273 --> 1:07:12.111
Well, from a distance, yeah.

1:07:12.194 --> 1:07:13.738
I mean, Rob,
you gotta understand, man.

1:07:13.821 --> 1:07:15.322
I was devastated.

1:07:15.406 --> 1:07:18.075
The love of my life,
my unborn child, both dead.

1:07:18.951 --> 1:07:20.494
It was hard, man. I--

1:07:21.704 --> 1:07:22.913
I had her cremated.

1:07:22.997 --> 1:07:26.083
Well, then, if she was cremated,
then you know she's not alive.

1:07:31.505 --> 1:07:33.716
-Chelsea.
-What?

1:07:33.799 --> 1:07:35.593
Like I said,
it was hard on me,

1:07:35.676 --> 1:07:38.596
so I had her best friend
Chelsea handle everything...

1:07:39.847 --> 1:07:41.849
including the cremation.

1:07:44.393 --> 1:07:47.480
What you're telling me
is that you aren't sure

1:07:47.563 --> 1:07:50.066
that she was actually cremated?

1:07:50.149 --> 1:07:52.985
Now, I can go this thing alone,
or I can get my guys on it,

1:07:53.069 --> 1:07:54.779
but it's gonna cost you
a lot of money.

1:07:56.989 --> 1:07:59.909
Money's not an issue, man.
Find her.

1:07:59.992 --> 1:08:01.160
All right. In the meantime,

1:08:01.243 --> 1:08:02.787
you need to get some help, brother.

1:08:09.085 --> 1:08:11.045
Long time, no see.

1:08:11.128 --> 1:08:12.129
Hey.

1:08:13.547 --> 1:08:15.299
It--It has been a minute.

1:08:16.509 --> 1:08:18.010
How are you?

1:08:18.094 --> 1:08:20.888
Ah, I'm okay, you know.

1:08:20.971 --> 1:08:23.474
Just taking it one day at a time.

1:08:25.559 --> 1:08:27.103
So come here. Come here.

1:08:31.232 --> 1:08:32.858
I know. It's been--

1:08:32.942 --> 1:08:36.654
It's been--
It's been hard, you know?

1:08:36.737 --> 1:08:41.033
I, um, I can't believe
I lost my best friend.

1:08:44.495 --> 1:08:47.665
So to what do I owe this pleasure?

1:08:47.748 --> 1:08:52.378
Uh, just wanna let you know
I'm selling the house.

1:08:52.461 --> 1:08:53.963
Uh, it would really mean a lot

1:08:54.046 --> 1:08:56.966
if you came by and helped
with Madison's things,

1:08:57.049 --> 1:08:58.300
if you want to.

1:08:58.384 --> 1:09:00.386
Yeah, sure.

1:09:00.469 --> 1:09:02.221
Sure. Just let me know when.

1:09:02.304 --> 1:09:04.181
Well, maybe tomorrow
you can come by,

1:09:04.265 --> 1:09:05.724
if you're not too busy.

1:09:05.808 --> 1:09:07.434
Okay, cool.

1:09:07.518 --> 1:09:09.061
All right. See you then.

1:09:10.020 --> 1:09:11.647
Michael.

1:09:11.730 --> 1:09:15.234
It's--It's really good
to see you doing good.

1:09:43.512 --> 1:09:44.972
[overlapping chatter]

1:09:45.055 --> 1:09:47.808
I like when you guys
work together.

1:09:47.892 --> 1:09:49.393
-You want another color?
-Yeah.

1:09:49.476 --> 1:09:51.228
-What about this one?
-Yeah, that's so pretty.

1:09:51.312 --> 1:09:54.523
-Yeah.
-[cellphone buzzing]

1:09:54.607 --> 1:09:57.026
I'm happy you came today.

1:09:57.109 --> 1:09:58.319
Ohh.

1:09:58.402 --> 1:10:01.030
My daddy really likes you.

1:10:01.113 --> 1:10:04.617
He does? Guess what?

1:10:04.700 --> 1:10:06.368
I really like your dad.

1:10:06.660 --> 1:10:07.828
And you, too.

1:10:08.537 --> 1:10:10.414
Can I tell you a secret?

1:10:10.497 --> 1:10:13.292
Of course.
You can tell me anything.

1:10:13.375 --> 1:10:15.794
[whispers]
I like you, too.

1:10:15.878 --> 1:10:17.504
You're so cute.

1:10:53.040 --> 1:10:54.458
Excuse me, miss?

1:10:54.541 --> 1:10:56.210
Can I help you?

1:11:01.131 --> 1:11:03.717
I've also followed up on the lead

1:11:03.801 --> 1:11:05.886
of that address that you gave me.

1:11:05.970 --> 1:11:08.305
Yeah, I know. I--I Googled it,

1:11:08.389 --> 1:11:10.849
but I figured that had to be a dead--
dead lead.

1:11:10.933 --> 1:11:12.476
It's a burger stand.
Why would she--

1:11:13.769 --> 1:11:17.606
Yeah, what you don't know
is that a couple of weeks ago,

1:11:17.690 --> 1:11:20.609
a woman started working there
that fits her description.

1:11:20.693 --> 1:11:22.528
My guy has looked into it.

1:11:25.489 --> 1:11:26.657
So we're on it.

1:11:28.033 --> 1:11:29.368
Don't worry about it. I got--

1:11:29.451 --> 1:11:30.995
I'll go look into that.
You don't have--

1:11:31.078 --> 1:11:32.621
No, no, you're not gonna look into it.

1:11:32.705 --> 1:11:34.915
That's what you paid us for, all right?

1:11:34.999 --> 1:11:37.209
Just let me do my job.

1:11:37.293 --> 1:11:41.714
Secondly, have you looked into
some kind of counseling, bro?

1:11:41.797 --> 1:11:44.174
-Yeah, I talked--
-Don't lie to me, man.

1:11:44.258 --> 1:11:46.260
I talked to somebody about it.

1:11:46.343 --> 1:11:48.262
I got that--
I got it under control.

1:11:48.345 --> 1:11:49.847
Don't worry about it.

1:11:53.100 --> 1:11:54.685
[car lock chirps]

1:11:56.103 --> 1:11:57.980
[bushes rustling]

1:12:02.234 --> 1:12:04.278
[bushes rustling]

1:12:07.239 --> 1:12:09.241
[footsteps]

1:12:11.952 --> 1:12:13.245
[screams]

1:12:13.329 --> 1:12:15.581
Whoa, it's just me.
It's just me.

1:12:15.664 --> 1:12:16.957
-Okay.
-You all right?

1:12:17.041 --> 1:12:18.417
Yes. I'm sorry.

1:12:18.500 --> 1:12:20.002
I'm sorry that I startled you.

1:12:20.085 --> 1:12:22.338
Yeah, no, no, no.
I'm fine.

1:12:22.421 --> 1:12:24.757
I just get a little paranoid
sometimes, you know...

1:12:24.840 --> 1:12:26.967
-Yeah.
-me in this house by myself.

1:12:27.051 --> 1:12:30.679
Okay. Well, you know,
you don't have to be.

1:12:30.763 --> 1:12:32.222
What does that mean?

1:12:32.306 --> 1:12:34.391
Alone in this house by yourself.

1:12:34.475 --> 1:12:36.352
Where's Rachel?

1:12:36.435 --> 1:12:38.437
Rachel, she's staying over
at her friend's,

1:12:38.562 --> 1:12:39.855
spending the night.

1:12:39.938 --> 1:12:41.482
Come on.

1:12:45.361 --> 1:12:46.278
Come on.

1:12:46.362 --> 1:12:47.363
[laughs] Okay.

1:12:54.370 --> 1:12:56.580
Damn.

1:12:56.663 --> 1:12:58.999
-[laughs]
-Sorry.

1:12:59.083 --> 1:13:01.293
You are even beautiful
in the morning.

1:13:01.377 --> 1:13:03.045
Oh, stop it.

1:13:03.128 --> 1:13:05.005
[laughs]

1:13:05.089 --> 1:13:06.673
Are you a witch?

1:13:06.757 --> 1:13:10.260
[laughs]
Trying to make me blush?

1:13:10.344 --> 1:13:12.763
Freaks me out a little bit.

1:13:12.846 --> 1:13:14.681
[sighs]

1:13:16.475 --> 1:13:19.478
Thank you...
for staying with me.

1:13:20.521 --> 1:13:23.857
It's been a long time
since I just talked, you know.

1:13:23.941 --> 1:13:25.234
I know, right?

1:13:26.902 --> 1:13:29.405
-Hope I didn't talk your ear off.
-No, you didn't.

1:13:30.697 --> 1:13:34.827
'Cause you fell asleep
in the middle of my last story.

1:13:34.910 --> 1:13:36.328
[laughs] I did?

1:13:36.412 --> 1:13:39.164
Mm-hmm. Yep.

1:13:39.248 --> 1:13:41.250
Oh. That's why--

1:13:41.333 --> 1:13:42.793
I'm sleeping for two, remember?

1:13:42.876 --> 1:13:44.753
It's all good.

1:13:46.130 --> 1:13:47.631
I had fun.

1:13:47.714 --> 1:13:49.174
Me, too.

1:13:50.634 --> 1:13:52.594
Gotta hit the head.
I'll be right back.

1:13:55.431 --> 1:13:56.974
[clears throat]

1:14:02.729 --> 1:14:04.731
[toilet flushing]

1:14:06.775 --> 1:14:07.776
[seat thumps]

1:14:13.031 --> 1:14:15.033
Did you just put the toilet seat down?

1:14:15.117 --> 1:14:17.327
Yeah.
Did I do something wrong?

1:14:18.829 --> 1:14:22.291
No, not at all.

1:14:22.374 --> 1:14:24.585
[chuckles]

1:14:24.668 --> 1:14:28.172
As a matter of fact,
you did everything right.

1:14:30.757 --> 1:14:32.593
Do you--Do you like me?

1:14:32.676 --> 1:14:34.845
I like doughnuts.

1:14:36.346 --> 1:14:37.681
Are you a doughnut?

1:14:37.764 --> 1:14:40.309
-Do you like doughnuts?
-Yes.

1:14:40.392 --> 1:14:42.060
[laughs]

1:14:47.524 --> 1:14:49.485
There you go.

1:14:51.111 --> 1:14:53.655
-Excuse me.
-Hi.

1:14:53.739 --> 1:14:56.825
My name's John.
I'm looking for Madison Roland.

1:14:56.909 --> 1:14:58.744
Madison Roland?

1:14:58.827 --> 1:15:00.537
There's nobody here by that name.

1:15:00.621 --> 1:15:01.997
You sure you're in the right place?

1:15:02.080 --> 1:15:04.917
Uh, yeah, this is the address
I was given.

1:15:05.000 --> 1:15:06.668
Yeah, sorry. No Madison here.

1:15:06.752 --> 1:15:08.795
That's strange.

1:15:08.879 --> 1:15:11.632
I'm her brother.
Our father's in the hospital.

1:15:11.715 --> 1:15:13.467
I just wanted to let her know about it.

1:15:13.550 --> 1:15:16.178
Um, I haven't seen her in years,
but I actually have a picture.

1:15:18.639 --> 1:15:20.140
That's Kate!

1:15:20.224 --> 1:15:21.391
Kate?

1:15:21.475 --> 1:15:23.060
Kate Smith. She works here.

1:15:23.143 --> 1:15:25.312
Kate.

1:15:25.437 --> 1:15:27.564
-Yeah.
-[chuckles]

1:15:27.648 --> 1:15:29.441
Well, I'm sorry about your father.

1:15:29.525 --> 1:15:31.443
Uh, you want me
to let her know you came by?

1:15:31.527 --> 1:15:32.861
I didn't catch your name.

1:15:32.945 --> 1:15:34.821
Do you happen to know
where she's staying?

1:15:34.905 --> 1:15:36.448
That, I can't help you with,

1:15:36.532 --> 1:15:39.243
but if you wanna check with
the elementary school down the street,

1:15:39.326 --> 1:15:41.203
her boyfriend teaches down there.

1:15:42.746 --> 1:15:44.915
Want me to write it down for you?

1:15:45.249 --> 1:15:46.583
No.

1:15:49.461 --> 1:15:51.421
So he came to visit you
out of nowhere?

1:15:51.505 --> 1:15:55.384
Yeah, and he wanted me to come
and help him pack your things.

1:15:55.467 --> 1:15:58.804
I don't know. Maybe--
Maybe you should help him,

1:15:58.887 --> 1:16:02.099
'cause we don't wanna give him
any signals that lead to me.

1:16:02.182 --> 1:16:04.893
I don't know. I mean,
it just felt strange, you know.

1:16:04.977 --> 1:16:07.437
I mean, I didn't even know
Michael knew where I lived.

1:16:07.521 --> 1:16:09.189
I mean, that is odd.

1:16:13.610 --> 1:16:15.612
[gasping]

1:16:17.573 --> 1:16:19.324
[groans]

1:16:21.076 --> 1:16:22.703
Oh, my gosh.

1:16:22.786 --> 1:16:24.621
What? What happened?

1:16:24.705 --> 1:16:27.499
I think my water just broke.

1:16:27.583 --> 1:16:29.501
A-Are you sure? Is--

1:16:29.585 --> 1:16:31.545
I think I'm going into labor.

1:16:31.628 --> 1:16:33.714
Right now?
Right now right now?

1:16:33.797 --> 1:16:35.382
Okay, I-I'm coming. I'm coming.

1:16:35.465 --> 1:16:37.342
I have to get my--
Okay, I-I'm coming.

1:16:37.426 --> 1:16:38.343
I'm on my way!

1:16:38.427 --> 1:16:39.553
Okay, hurry.

1:16:41.597 --> 1:16:43.599
[groaning, breathing heavily]

1:16:52.858 --> 1:16:54.818
Alex.

1:16:54.901 --> 1:16:57.362
[music playing]

1:17:03.660 --> 1:17:06.038
[music playing only]

1:17:42.366 --> 1:17:44.701
[baby crying]

1:17:57.923 --> 1:17:59.257
[Chelsea] You were amazing.

1:17:59.341 --> 1:18:00.717
[Madison] Oh, thank you.

1:18:00.801 --> 1:18:02.552
If I ever find myself in that position,

1:18:02.636 --> 1:18:03.845
I'd be like, "Hey!"

1:18:03.929 --> 1:18:05.597
Oh, you will, honey, with that hair.

1:18:05.681 --> 1:18:06.973
[laughs] No.

1:18:08.934 --> 1:18:11.645
We'll get you somebody
in here for sure.

1:18:11.728 --> 1:18:13.605
So how does it feel
to be a mommy?

1:18:15.023 --> 1:18:19.027
Amazing and exhausting.
[chuckles]

1:18:19.111 --> 1:18:21.363
-He's a lucky kid.
-Oh.

1:18:21.446 --> 1:18:22.864
-[Chelsea] He's beautiful.
-Thank you.

1:18:22.948 --> 1:18:23.949
[laughs]

1:18:25.534 --> 1:18:26.785
You, too.

1:18:26.868 --> 1:18:29.454
God, you're gonna be
an amazing mom.

1:18:29.538 --> 1:18:31.289
He is lucky.

1:19:04.781 --> 1:19:07.743
[ambulance siren blaring]

1:19:10.704 --> 1:19:12.706
[chatter outside]

1:19:52.204 --> 1:19:55.332
Look who decided to wake up.

1:19:56.541 --> 1:19:57.876
Did you guys just get back?

1:19:57.959 --> 1:19:59.544
We just came
from the vending machines.

1:20:00.587 --> 1:20:02.506
-Got your favorite.
-That's not my favorite.

1:20:02.589 --> 1:20:03.924
I know. They're mine.

1:20:04.007 --> 1:20:05.675
Um, I didn't know what to get you, so...

1:20:05.759 --> 1:20:06.927
You can have that.

1:20:07.010 --> 1:20:08.887
-[laughs]
-I've got a long drive.

1:20:08.970 --> 1:20:11.556
-I'm gonna head back, okay?
-Okay.

1:20:11.640 --> 1:20:14.017
You let me know if you need me
to bring you anything,

1:20:14.100 --> 1:20:15.602
-anything at all.
-I will.

1:20:15.685 --> 1:20:17.395
-Okay.
-Thank you.

1:20:17.479 --> 1:20:18.730
Mm.

1:20:18.814 --> 1:20:19.940
-I love you.
-I love you.

1:20:20.023 --> 1:20:21.608
[laughs] Jinx.

1:20:21.691 --> 1:20:24.903
-Oh.
-Oh, my little baby maker.

1:20:24.986 --> 1:20:27.113
Tell that baby
that Aunt Chelsea says hello.

1:20:27.197 --> 1:20:29.199
I'm gonna give him
a big kiss from you.

1:20:29.282 --> 1:20:30.826
-Please do.
-Text me when you get home.

1:20:30.909 --> 1:20:33.078
I will, absolutely. Love you.

1:20:33.161 --> 1:20:35.038
-I love you.
-How you feeling?

1:20:35.121 --> 1:20:36.039
[Doctor] Oh. Hey, Chelsea.

1:20:36.122 --> 1:20:37.499
Oh, here she is!

1:20:37.582 --> 1:20:41.586
Okay, Kate.
You and Alex are all set to go.

1:20:41.670 --> 1:20:45.215
Your baby boy is very healthy,
seven pounds, six ounces.

1:20:52.222 --> 1:20:53.306
[sighs]

1:21:04.693 --> 1:21:06.319
[gasps] Oh, jeez.

1:21:06.403 --> 1:21:08.405
We just need your signature right here.

1:21:10.490 --> 1:21:12.158
Did you think of a name yet?

1:21:12.242 --> 1:21:14.744
I know one of the nurses
said you were undecided.

1:21:14.828 --> 1:21:16.496
Peace.

1:21:17.581 --> 1:21:18.790
His name will be Peace.

1:21:18.874 --> 1:21:20.083
That's beautiful.

1:21:20.166 --> 1:21:21.626
I wish you the best.

1:21:21.710 --> 1:21:23.128
-Thank you, Doctor.
-Thanks a lot, Doc.

1:21:23.211 --> 1:21:24.671
Sure.

1:21:24.754 --> 1:21:25.714
Peace?

1:21:25.797 --> 1:21:26.715
Yeah.

1:21:26.798 --> 1:21:28.216
That's all right.

1:21:28.300 --> 1:21:30.635
Wanna go get Peace
so we can get outta here?

1:21:33.680 --> 1:21:34.931
There you go.

1:21:39.144 --> 1:21:41.771
Yes, so how you feeling?

1:21:41.855 --> 1:21:43.815
-You all right?
-A little tired.

1:21:43.899 --> 1:21:45.567
-Yeah, that was a lot.
-I'm tired.

1:21:45.650 --> 1:21:47.986
Yeah, you were working hard in there.

1:21:48.069 --> 1:21:49.738
We're all right.

1:21:51.448 --> 1:21:52.866
-This dude, he's gonna be...
-We tried.

1:21:52.949 --> 1:21:54.451
a good sleeper.

1:21:54.534 --> 1:21:55.535
Is he?

1:21:55.619 --> 1:21:57.746
Yeah. He is out.

1:21:58.955 --> 1:22:00.248
Here we go.

1:22:01.291 --> 1:22:03.877
All right.

1:22:03.960 --> 1:22:06.338
Sweet dreams, buddy.

1:22:07.422 --> 1:22:08.590
He's beautiful.

1:22:09.841 --> 1:22:11.343
-He says thank you.
-[laughs]

1:22:11.426 --> 1:22:17.349
Hey, why don't you and Peace
come over tonight?

1:22:17.432 --> 1:22:19.726
I'll get a blanket.
We could have a little--

1:22:19.809 --> 1:22:21.519
little living room picnic.

1:22:21.603 --> 1:22:23.480
I know Rachel would love
to meet little dude,

1:22:23.563 --> 1:22:27.192
and--and I give really good
foot massages.

1:22:28.485 --> 1:22:30.028
I'm gonna take you up on that offer.

1:22:30.111 --> 1:22:33.782
Excellent.
That's wonderful, wonderful news.

1:22:33.865 --> 1:22:36.618
I'm just gonna freshen up,
pack a small bag.

1:22:36.701 --> 1:22:40.622
Okay, cool.
Cool, cool, cool. Okay.

1:22:40.705 --> 1:22:43.083
Oh, lemon meringue...

1:22:43.166 --> 1:22:44.793
I'll bring the ice cream, yes.

1:22:44.876 --> 1:22:46.670
Yes! All right.

1:22:46.753 --> 1:22:48.338
-Hey, Alex?
-Yeah?

1:22:48.421 --> 1:22:51.591
Um, thank you so much.

1:22:51.675 --> 1:22:53.176
For what?

1:22:54.469 --> 1:22:56.137
For everything.

1:22:56.221 --> 1:22:58.181
For, uh...

1:22:58.264 --> 1:22:59.182
Yeah.

1:22:59.265 --> 1:23:00.350
Is this happening?

1:23:10.694 --> 1:23:12.028
All right.

1:23:12.112 --> 1:23:14.656
-I'm gonna be waiting over there for you.
-Okay.

1:23:14.739 --> 1:23:15.824
Don't forget that ice cream.

1:23:15.907 --> 1:23:17.492
-I won't. I will not.
-Okay.

1:23:18.743 --> 1:23:19.828
All right.

1:23:21.579 --> 1:23:23.957
Wow. Okay.

1:23:24.040 --> 1:23:26.501
That's what I'm talking about.

1:23:26.584 --> 1:23:28.211
[chuckles]

1:23:55.780 --> 1:23:58.158
[dog barks]

1:23:58.241 --> 1:24:01.119
[lullaby plays]

1:24:09.335 --> 1:24:11.296
[shower running]

1:24:22.182 --> 1:24:23.850
[clatter]

1:24:23.933 --> 1:24:25.393
[turns off water]

1:24:26.770 --> 1:24:27.729
[door closes]

1:24:27.812 --> 1:24:29.147
Alex?

1:24:44.913 --> 1:24:46.581
Alex?

1:24:54.339 --> 1:24:55.757
Alex?

1:25:04.349 --> 1:25:05.934
Alex?

1:25:07.268 --> 1:25:09.479
Alex, is that you?

1:25:30.583 --> 1:25:31.960
[stereo playing
"For the Love of You"]

1:25:32.043 --> 1:25:33.253
♪ Yeah ♪

1:25:34.462 --> 1:25:36.631
♪ Well, well, well ♪

1:25:36.714 --> 1:25:38.466
♪ Yeah ♪

1:25:41.845 --> 1:25:43.096
♪ Yeah ♪

1:25:43.805 --> 1:25:46.224
♪ Yeah ♪

1:25:49.269 --> 1:25:51.312
♪ Ooh ♪

1:25:51.396 --> 1:25:54.816
♪ Drifting on a memory ♪

1:25:56.276 --> 1:25:58.820
♪ Ain't no place I'd rather be ♪

1:25:58.903 --> 1:26:01.447
-Come on. Stupid Bluetooth.
-♪ Than with you ♪

1:26:01.531 --> 1:26:02.991
♪ Yeah ♪
[music stops]

1:26:07.120 --> 1:26:09.122
[breathing heavily]

1:26:10.665 --> 1:26:12.876
Get it together, Madison.
Come on.

1:26:12.959 --> 1:26:14.961
[lullaby playing]

1:26:35.732 --> 1:26:37.108
Peace.

1:26:41.029 --> 1:26:43.615
[piano playing
"For the Love of You"]

1:27:08.973 --> 1:27:10.767
He loves this song.

1:27:12.185 --> 1:27:13.394
Michael.

1:27:16.731 --> 1:27:20.526
Michael,
please don't hurt my baby.

1:27:23.988 --> 1:27:26.282
I would never do anything
to hurt him.

1:27:30.161 --> 1:27:32.038
Right, buddy?

1:27:34.290 --> 1:27:35.750
Hey, okay.

1:27:40.171 --> 1:27:41.589
You're right.

1:27:43.716 --> 1:27:45.260
Give him to me.

1:27:47.720 --> 1:27:49.597
He needs his rest.

1:27:52.475 --> 1:27:54.686
It's okay, son. Daddy's here.

1:28:03.653 --> 1:28:04.696
Come here.

1:28:04.779 --> 1:28:06.197
Shh, shh, shh.

1:28:06.281 --> 1:28:08.283
Shh, shh, shh, shh.

1:28:08.366 --> 1:28:10.368
[Peace fussing]

1:28:15.415 --> 1:28:17.750
I missed you so much, Madison.

1:28:21.671 --> 1:28:23.423
Why not put the baby
back in his room?

1:28:23.506 --> 1:28:25.717
We don't have much time.
We have to go home now.

1:28:39.647 --> 1:28:41.649
[Peace fussing]

1:28:59.751 --> 1:29:01.169
Mmm.

1:29:02.962 --> 1:29:05.089
You smell like the day we met.

1:29:07.800 --> 1:29:11.596
You know, you forgot something.

1:29:18.061 --> 1:29:19.687
Michael, what are you doing?

1:29:19.771 --> 1:29:21.606
Shh.

1:29:21.689 --> 1:29:23.191
No.

1:29:25.777 --> 1:29:27.278
Don't do that.

1:29:32.992 --> 1:29:35.078
I brought your favorite dress.

1:29:36.412 --> 1:29:38.915
Why don't you go put it on?

1:29:38.998 --> 1:29:40.500
No.

1:29:40.583 --> 1:29:42.293
Put it on.

1:29:48.257 --> 1:29:50.093
You have any idea
what I've been through

1:29:50.176 --> 1:29:51.427
the last couple of months?

1:29:51.511 --> 1:29:54.472
You let me believe you were dead.

1:29:57.266 --> 1:29:58.601
Put the dress on.

1:30:04.941 --> 1:30:06.442
Dead.

1:30:09.153 --> 1:30:13.157
No matter what I did
or where I went,

1:30:13.241 --> 1:30:18.663
all I could think about
was I killed my wife.

1:30:21.124 --> 1:30:22.250
[chuckles]

1:30:24.001 --> 1:30:27.380
And I blamed myself for it
every single day.

1:30:29.215 --> 1:30:30.299
Every day.

1:30:32.093 --> 1:30:35.304
You made a joke out of me, didn't you?

1:30:35.388 --> 1:30:38.599
And then I come to find out you're alive.

1:30:38.683 --> 1:30:41.227
I really did not mean to hurt you.

1:30:49.986 --> 1:30:51.654
[knock on door]

1:30:58.161 --> 1:31:01.873
If you do anything strange,
one single thing,

1:31:01.956 --> 1:31:03.791
I will kill him.

1:31:03.875 --> 1:31:05.376
[knock on door]

1:31:06.377 --> 1:31:07.420
Go get the door.

1:31:10.923 --> 1:31:13.217
Go get the door.

1:31:25.021 --> 1:31:26.063
Hey, beautiful.

1:31:26.147 --> 1:31:27.648
Hey.

1:31:27.732 --> 1:31:29.817
Uh, Rachel and I are over there
waiting on you.

1:31:29.901 --> 1:31:32.737
Hey, Alex.
I was on my way over,

1:31:32.820 --> 1:31:35.156
but, um, I had
to take care of some things.

1:31:35.239 --> 1:31:37.200
Okay. Cool.

1:31:37.283 --> 1:31:39.744
Well, the foot massage
is calling your name.

1:31:39.827 --> 1:31:41.913
Uh, I just wanted to make sure
everything was cool,

1:31:41.996 --> 1:31:43.539
'cause I texted you a couple of times.

1:31:43.623 --> 1:31:45.166
-You didn't respond.
-Yeah, I was, uh,

1:31:45.249 --> 1:31:48.127
taking a bath and relaxing.

1:31:48.211 --> 1:31:51.047
I lost track of time.
My phone was on the charger.

1:31:51.130 --> 1:31:53.341
Got it.

1:31:53.424 --> 1:31:54.550
Okay.

1:31:54.634 --> 1:31:57.303
I'm gonna stay in tonight.

1:31:57.386 --> 1:31:59.555
I'm really exhausted.

1:32:01.599 --> 1:32:03.809
Okay, all right.

1:32:03.893 --> 1:32:04.894
I understand.

1:32:04.977 --> 1:32:07.063
Um, you sure you're okay?

1:32:07.146 --> 1:32:08.689
'Cause me and Rachel,
we can come over.

1:32:08.773 --> 1:32:09.774
I'm fine.

1:32:10.775 --> 1:32:12.610
Oh, I appreciate the offer.

1:32:12.693 --> 1:32:15.488
Okay. You know,
Rachel's gonna be mad.

1:32:15.571 --> 1:32:17.281
You give her a kiss for me?

1:32:17.365 --> 1:32:19.325
I will do.

1:32:19.408 --> 1:32:21.285
All right. Good night.

1:32:21.369 --> 1:32:22.578
Okay.

1:32:22.662 --> 1:32:24.121
Flake.

1:32:35.007 --> 1:32:36.008
Good girl.

1:32:38.844 --> 1:32:40.346
You got your family.

1:33:09.625 --> 1:33:11.961
[Michael yelling]

1:33:17.174 --> 1:33:18.509
[Madison] Stop! Stop!

1:33:18.592 --> 1:33:20.928
[grunting]

1:33:24.515 --> 1:33:25.725
[Michael grunting]

1:33:25.808 --> 1:33:28.602
Michael, stop!

1:33:28.686 --> 1:33:30.313
Stop.

1:33:30.396 --> 1:33:33.065
Michael! Stop!

1:33:38.195 --> 1:33:39.405
Please.

1:33:42.825 --> 1:33:45.286
He has nothing to do with this.

1:33:50.041 --> 1:33:52.668
If you kill him,
you'll--you'll go away,

1:33:52.752 --> 1:33:57.298
and you--
you can't take care of me.

1:33:57.381 --> 1:33:59.383
[panting]

1:34:09.101 --> 1:34:10.394
You're right.

1:34:13.522 --> 1:34:16.609
This man can't protect you.

1:34:20.821 --> 1:34:23.324
